\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Both your parents came from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 nold{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Both of 'em. In fact me mother's father were - the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Arnold
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} carrier in them days, but I can't remember it you know, it were afore my day. Then he did go to live at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Sheffield{\*\xmlclose} - after. 'Cos I went to see him a time or two up there, up at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Sheffield{\*\xmlclose}. But - but anyway you can put 'em down as {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Arnold{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Where were you actually born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Derrymount. Just top side of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Arnold{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Me dad lived in it over fifty years. I lived in it 'til I was twenty-eight. Got married from there at twenty-eight I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So what year were you actually married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 1922.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And you had eight brothers and six sisters, do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When he were - when I was born? I could 
work it out. He was eighty-three when he died in - 1939. And I - I were born - what should I be at thirty-nine - thirty-nine and six. That'd be forty-five. So - I should be forty-five when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 He was forty-five when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Yes, that'd be it I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What was his job then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 He was a miner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was he at the coalface?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Yes. Coalface, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Is there a special name for that job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, not at that time there wasn't. He was just - just at the coalface. Some of them were c
alled rippers and - that but the - the majority was what they call a coalface worker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he have another job before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I never heard him say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he have another job after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 He may have done. No. No, he never had another job after it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No, I never remember him being out of work, I remember him being - often short you know, short time, lot of short time - in his working life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Which pits was he working at in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Up to - as far as I can remember back he worked at Bestwood. But he did - I know he had worked at Lynby, had worked a bit a Lynby - in his younger days. But he were - from me knowing him it were at Bestwood. And he finished up at Bestwood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well my mother were seventy when she died. And she died in - '31. So put six onto thirty-one. That was my - that'd be how old her should be wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And she came from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Arnold{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} too?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did she have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I never heard her say - anything about her job, I've never heard. I don't know really what she done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did she ever work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did she ever do any work at home or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh she used to do all the housework but - never done - she got plenty -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No paid work at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No work - no other than housework have I - have I ever seen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How many rooms were there in the house, the house at Derrymount?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well there were three bedrooms. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 house place}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 , the kitchen we used to call it. Then there was what we called - back - back kitchen, which was like a scullery with - with bigger room than what they have now like. But there were no water in.
 We used to have to fetch it from the spring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was that far?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - some'd think it were a long way but I - we didn't used to - think so, it was about as far as bottom of this street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 A hundred yards or so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Used to fetch it from t
here. I remember 'em having water put in, getting water in, I think I should be about - I weren't very old, about eight - eight perhaps. And it cost 'em tuppence a week - to have water put in then. And - the house were only half a crown. So it went up to 
two and eight. And we'd got a big garden. And me dad used to keep pigs and fowls, so - we'd got plenty of room like, outside, not much in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have a front room or was that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 house place}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh that was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 houseplace that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  was it, that's where we lived in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did the door open straight into that room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Yes. Aye. Soon as you opened door you were in the - living room as you might say. Then the little passage to the back door. Back door used to come out onto - where {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Churchmore Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} is now. Where they've built them new houses on top of - just on top of that first hill, that's where our house stood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was it a very old one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well, it were pretty old, it weren't - weren't no - I bet it'd be - well above hundred - hundred year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there anyone apart from you and your brothers and sisters living in the house, any aunts or anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. Never nobody else. There were no room for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did anyone other than the family help in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well we all - we all used t
o help. Yes, I can remember when we used to mop floors and - or anything, if I were off work or ill. We used to help and do - if a job wanted doing we did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were little what tasks did you have to do to help at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I used to - look after pigs a bit and - fowls. Bit of gardening. Same as I tell you, bit of housework for me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of housework would you have done as a boy in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 mop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 floor or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have a special sort of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Or did you just do what was asked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, we used to take it in us stride, what wanted doing, no special -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How long did you continue doing these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well, I took to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 To leaving home or leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well not so much 
leaving home because we'd got three younger sisters do you see as they - they took to the - chores as I were doing you see. But - you could say up to - starting work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did the girls do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They used to help - help same and do bit of - bit of me
nding and bit of - darning or anything, bit of housework you know. Anything that wanted doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In your family were there sort of girls jobs and boys jobs or did you all do everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh yes. You see - while I - in my - well young life we'll say
, as a lad, you see I'd got no sisters - older, so I got - so I got a sister's job. At times you see, what I mean, a girls job - often. Well then - there were three - three or four - three following mea bit sharp, the three girls followed me a bit sharp. 
Mary and Hilda. Mary and Hilda, now - there were two - two followed me. So they took me off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did the older children help the younger ones with things they found difficult, like dressing the little ones?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh they used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 help one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  another. Oh they 
all used to help. Take 'em out, they - they never had a pram. Never had a pram. Never had a pram while they were married. And they only had one cradle. And me dad used to mend - keep mending it up, it were big wooden'n. And when it went - rockers went wro
ng he'd put a new rocker on it, made it keep managing. But we never did have a pram, I've heard 'em - say theirselves about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did the younger children help the older children in any ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well they used to - take 'em out - walks and - I've be
en - as many as five on 'em and me around Lime Lane and take 'em out and that and - used to look after 'em as best we could you know. Oh it were - we were brought up to it you see, we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well there were none sent out. It was all done at home. By somebody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother or father make or mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Mother used to mend 'em and make 'em and all. Mend and - make - make and mend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were the clothes new or secondhand in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well pretty near always new but - the - but we - we had to have it for a Sunday suit - for so long be - before we wore it any other day. It was always the Sunday suit which - we did always have a Sunday suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Where did you buy clothes in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well while I was a lad we were buying of Mrs Dews at that shop where that cafe thing is now, that - on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Front Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Corner of - one way street you know. That's where we used to go to have us suits fitted, when we were lads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well we used to get shoes at - Redford's and - and Marshall's - Mr Marshall's up - Front Street, next door to the - that - pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You got them in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Arnold{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Got 1 got 'em in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Arnold{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Oh yes - they didn't used to - go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Nottingham{\*\xmlclose} for much. Got 'em in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Arnold{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your father help your mother with any jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well he used to have - pretty - pretty busy enough without. You know what I mean - he used to let children help. He'd got three - three gardens growing vegetables u
p Spout Lane and his garden at home and - being away - been at the pit so he was busy enough weren't he.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 He virtually didn't do any help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I can't say as he didn't but - you know what I mean, if things were carrying on normal, he - he'd get on with his own - jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would he do things like fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh he'd make fire in the morning. Oh aye, he'd make fires and - all look after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Decorating in the house at all would he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, now decorating at that time of 
day it wasn't same as today. He used to get started - top, with a bucket and it were blue. Then he used to go and - room when he come to put a bit of - what do you call it - pink - in the same bucket do you see. That's how they decorated then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would he do the whole house every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, used to it about every year. Aye. In his way you know. Aye. But it were - it were only like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 lime washing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  it, in a way of speaking. You see, it was just - just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 lime washing}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 . That's all you could put it down to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would he do repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, he never done repairs, that were - landlord's job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he do any improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. He couldn't hardly. There were hardly any way we could improve on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were little did he dress you or undress you, the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No, they used to all undress theirselves and - look after theirselves. Take their jacket and waistcoat off and off upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your father ever read to you when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, he couldn't read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he ever go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
My mother learnt him what bit of - what - what bit of reading he could do. And it - it was getting on his later - latter part of life that he learnt that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he ever go t
o school did you say? If I tell you - his life at school, it - it'll want half a day. And he had to pay ha'penny. And he got sacked. For falling out with teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They wouldn't have him back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They wouldn't have him. That was up - that's pulled d
own there now, where they used to have council - down in - on - meadow there. Do you know meadow? Near {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Nottingham Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Council used to have that - place for a storeroom. That was school - then. And they paid - paid ha'penny a time. Ha'penny a - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How old was he when he went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
I don't know - I don't - he never told me how old he were. But he got - they told him he were - he were finished. And he'd only been once. That was all his - that was schooling as he got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, used to take us - not far mind you. We didn't get - if we went out - out for us holidays it were only to Trentbridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your father look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, looked after us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Pretty near. Aye, pretty near. Always to bed early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember what time it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh round }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  seven and - in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 winter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  perhaps a bit earlier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, we went - we put our - ourselves to bed after we got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How soon did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh we had - we went up - well we went up 'til, up like from being about six.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you share a bed with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When I were a lad I shared it with six. Aye. There in a bed. Bed were fitted up to one another. End to end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who did you have in yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 The three lads that - three - there elder lads in that - that end and three young ones in this one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did the others all fit in? Had some left home by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
We were never all at home together you know. Not the fifteen. When - when our Will and Lucy - had left - they'd left home before I were - Jim, Emma and them was born you know. You could average 
it - there'd be at least then - ten to twelve - at home - together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did the others sit in for sleeping when you were three in a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What, in - in same room? We used to sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 That's six of you, where did the others sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh, then - then the girls had this - room, that we used to have to go }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 
through}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 it. You see, it was - there was - going through and then there's another set. Attic that was where we was you know. Then - then there was two beds in there room but one were - there and
 one here you see. And sometimes there'd be - three - three and two. You see. Three in that one and - two in that. That's how they used to do it. But - then in my mother's room, mother and dad's - he made a - a bad as fit in corner. And he got this balsa 
and bored a hole in and - roped it and - made it fit corner for it to sleep two or three children. Like that. That's he worked it with his children - his younger children - youngest children like. I can remember that, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And this one wooden cradle for the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We got that fitted downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was it one you could rock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, it'd be big heavy rocker. Big heavy rocking - cradle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What room did you bath in at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We used to have a bath in - bath where we could. There 
were no bathroom. We had one of them - we had a big tin bath and - for the young 'uns they used to bath on - the hearth and for older 'uns used to - stop back or get up - in morning or anything best service we could find you see for it. But when we worked
 at pit - we used to strip down and go in a bath in a - in the kitchen - scullery like place. Kitchen we used to call it. Back kitchen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were a schoolchild how often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh mother bathed us regular. When we were - when we - bathed ourselves, we - we - we - should went one at - one a week anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was it a special day, was it a great ceremony?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 It were Friday night, when we were younger. Friday night when we were - bathed together like. Friday night were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When did you have clean clothes put on at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh we used to have clean clothes every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was this on a special day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Sunday morning. Mostly Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh had it in that one room of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room? Did you ever have a standing up meal in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. No, not very often. Used to make do in there. We used to - perhaps two or three sittings you know. Perhaps - you s
ee the - you - them as were in, then they'd perhaps - go out and others - sit down. We weren't same as them - them children when - when they said, what day is it tomorrow Florrie? She said, Sunday, oh dinner on plates. Ah we always got a dinner, I'll give
 - give my mother and father that credit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did she cook on a range like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Was just same as this. Used to have to boil our clothes and everything on that. Used to have one of them - chain wi' a hook on, to hang a pan on. For - for boiling the washing. No coppers - then. No copper in here anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you get extra coal in those days because your father was a miner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well we got - we got - we got coal - cheaper. Cheaper - he could }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 haul}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  it - haul it to where you wanted - after so long lik
e, if you could manage another - you didn't - didn't order but if you - if you wanted it you could order - I think it was about every five week. At that time of day. A load every five weeks, and it were only a few shillings. Four - four and sixpence to fi
ve shilling at the most. Aye. Mind you that were miners, see. Well - coal were only fivepence a hundred at that time you know. Only fivepence a hundredweight. Anyone could buy it at fivepence hundredweight.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When was breakfast eaten in your family, where did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We used to have it there - in that same room. As we got up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did you usually have to eat and drink at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh we used to get some decent food. About - about - about always a bit of bacon and egg in the
 morning or - or - or bacon and tomatoes. We used to have our own poultry like. If we were a bit short of eggs we used to have -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487  fried}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  tomatoes. - Used to always have a good breakfast. Oh aye. And plenty of bread yes - Mother used to take a stone every day
. Stone of bread. Aye. Yes, me dad made a shelf for it. In this back - kitchen. Baker used to come and put - there were yesterday's there and he used to move it up, put that, then mother used to always keep a day in hand you see. Day in hand bread. Stone 
a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So she didn't bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. She did if it were necessary. I've known her to bake. I've known her to bake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So you always had a proper breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You had it as you got up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We always pretty near had - had proper meals. We were - we never went hungry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What was the next meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Dinner. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What time would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - when we come from school. If - if we were at school or - them as were - went to work, there'd perhaps
 be two or three times for dinner. At that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of dinner did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Stewpot and - boiled pudding. We always used to get a good - good meals. She used to put - two - two roly puds in boiler. Sprags we used to call 'em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Roly dumplings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What are sprags?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Ah well, we named 'em sprags because - they were same shape as what - miner's sprag is - sprag is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What was a sprag though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, we - we called 'em sprags, because when they pulled out of
 boiler - they were same shape as miner's sprags as he pegged his coal up with. Well it were lump of wood. Aye, about that - that - so long you know and - and - that - that thick, you see, and these dumplings were same when - so we named 'em sprags. Then 
we used to have suety dumplings and - milk - tapioca and - if it were milk puddings we used to fetch us milk from that farm - Huckaby's farm it was then, just be going up to Bestwood - not the Hall, on Bestwood Park. What we used to call 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Bestwood{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Then
. And we used to take a - bucket - bit littler than that one there - and he'd fill it for you for - for a penny. Of milk. What they call it. Aye. That's what they used to make us milk puddings with then. Then when you're coming back he'd give you a turnip
. Aye. Aye. He said, pick - pick one of them me lad. Take one of them with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So you had a big meal in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well, tea. Then we didn't bother - very often bother with supper. Used to have a tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of things did you have for tea then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh used to - sometimes bread and jam and bread and butter. Perhaps a bit of cheese or anything of that you know, but of course - now elaborate. Just ordinary - ordinary tea like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And that was the end of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 That was end of the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did you drink mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Tea. Tea. And herb beer when me dad made it. Me dad used to always make it in summer. Herb beer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did everybody have breakfast or did some go off to work before breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - me dad were very - he wouldn't let 'em go to work without breakfast. No. You'd got to have their breakfast. He used to get up - if one were getting up early he'd be up - up to see that he had his breakfast. Yes, he wouldn't let - he 
wouldn't let nobody go without - out breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your father work shifts in those days or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No, there weren't much shift work. There were no - there were no afternoons at that time, there were days and night and he didn't - pretty near alw
ays had day. Night men were like what they call repair men at that time of day. Well now you see they all - they all go in shift - on all jobs. Pretty near all of 'em. They take coal - on both shifts, well at that time they weren't taking coal on afternoo
n shift. Well they were working nine hour shifts you know then. Oh yes, at the pit. Aye, nine hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have anything different to eat on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh well - bit better - bit of - have a bit of a roast beef and - vegetables and - and that. Wel
l we got vegetables on other days but we got - little bit special like on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 She used to make her own jam and - and - and bottle fruit and - all that - sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, pickled onions, pickled cabbage. Piccalilli. She'd make all her own pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And your father brewed beer, did anyone make any wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No, didn't make no wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Me dad used to look after that. Aye.
 He used to - he got your medicine. Every Sunday - every Sunday morning - he'd be up - up at half past five, and he'd been round - round - or picked 'em up coming from work and got his herbs. And he used to mash 'em every Sunday morning and you'd got to h
ave half - half a pint mug before you had anything to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you know what herbs they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No. Never knew what he got in. But I know we had one and - and rue and all that sort were all mashed in together. That's what he did.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did it taste nice or horrible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well it - yes, it would - what you call nice. 'Cos one of my sister's, she's only got a ha'penny, and she said, I'll give you a ha'penny to drink mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Ha'penny - ha'penny was money then. And he used to make us beer with them sort of things. Herb beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he make nettle beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Nettle and bitter nettles and bits of raspberry tops and - all sorts of - bit off of the hedge, hawthorn hedge. He'd put that - I can remember him when he used to make them. Hawthorn, bit of - young hawthorn. Burdock. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 Dandelion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 . Oh yes, put anything in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did he grow in the garden in the way of vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh practically everything. Aye. Potatoes, all sorts of vegetables. Everything, leeks, onions, anything that would grow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he grow fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Apples and plums. He had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they have to buy any vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - we used to average it out that he got enough - vegetables to last us - about two third of year. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  the rest of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We used to have to buy then - buy then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother buy fruit at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, what they got. Used to buy it. But you could get it pretty cheap then you know. All fruit. You see, me dad had got three - what
 they called club gardens up - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Spout Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, beside that one at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Three extra ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Three. Three hundred yards each. So that were nine hundred yards as he were - as he were gardening - for his - vegetables and - gooseberries and all that sort 
of - raspberries. Apple tree or two. And a plum. And then - then he - we used to have to buy what - what other things we want, well we - well we used to go gathering blackberries. Mother used to make blackberry jam and blackberry and apple. We used to gat
her those you see, what we could.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you say you occasionally had a pig?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, we had - we had - me dad bred pigs. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you ever have a goat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. No. Never had no goat. I don't think - don't think no more than a duck and a rabbit. And fowls. Had rabbit or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who looked after them mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 Mostly the lads just at a certain age. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
About - just leaving - before leaving school age they were - they took that job over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh
 usually had a bit of meat every day. Oh aye, a bit, if it were only - if it were only those four penn'orth of bits, it was - it were - you got a bit. Made a stewpot on it anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have tinned meat ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Very little. Very little tinned stuff. In fact - I think we only had tinned tomatoes. At that time of day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you ever get any extra meat from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 From where? Do you mean - a rabbit. We got rabbit or two - odd time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who did they come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I know he used t
o get - some for me mother, like when he were up at Bestwood. When - when they were beat - when they were shooting. He'd get my mother one or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there any poaching going on in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Arnold{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, there were plenty went poaching but we never we
nt poaching. We went - we weren't fetching now. Only what were - same as they were - blackberries or anything like that. If we took anything home - me dad'd make you take it back. Wherever you had got it from. And if you'd got it on the off chance you dar
esn't take it, you know, so we never offered to take anything home. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Remember what? Oh I - in a way of speaking I - I can remember her going without certain th
ings - so as the children could have it. But she wouldn't exactly go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Meat or anything like that, if there weren't quite - if there weren't much. If anyone went short it were mother. In the family like. She'd stint herself 
sooner than - pinch them. But she didn't exactly go without. But I - I've seen her - make a bit of a - squeeze, you see, like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your father have more than the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, he used to have a - a good meal and - perhaps had a few more 
- vegetables with being - that he could eat more of that but he didn't have - he didn't have no extra joint to himself. No. Oh no, he never - he always used to - have what bits we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, we were allowed to talk. Weren't allowed to - get out of no order you know or anything of that but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But you could talk at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Some families weren't allowed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Pretty near - pretty near you had to have what they give you. And if you - if - if you didn't eat that - you didn't get no other course. And - if you left too much, it'd be there for you when you come again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did this really happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Yes. For as - for as to make 'em - know as they got - looked after. That were way it were, how it were done. There were no - I don't like that. No, no. You never - you never heard none of 'em say, I don't like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 If there was something on the table you wanted, like salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye. You could ask - or - or reach for it, you pretty near reach it 'cos it weren't - far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, if we'd got any. Pretty near always have a second help - helping, if you had few vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, they didn't bother - about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Pretty near make best of your road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you bring toys or a book to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. There were no room for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you finished, you didn't wait on one another. Well somebody else would be waiting to sit down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So you couldn't all sit at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. No, couldn't all sit together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We was all in together there'd be two sittings. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who had the first sitting and who the second?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well, they used to take 'em in ages. Aye, take 'em in ages. The oldest. Oldest - according to when they go out, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you always have the same place at table? What order woul
d you be served in? At one sitting would you be served oldest first or youngest first or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - followed the same routine. Oldest first. Come}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 down in ages. Mother and father - if they were in. Both in. Then the oldest - in - and then when they got up - then if - perhaps if they were in late in the eldest have the - biggest plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When the younger brothers and sisters were small where did they sit before they could feed themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - mother'd have - if they were very young mother
'd have one on knee - and then the - we didn't have no high chair or nothing of that. They used to do - wait 'til - they were old enough to - sit in what - one of the other chairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who fed them, would your mother feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, or - or one of the oldest children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would the eldest boys help with things like this or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - no, there were mostly a girl in - take that job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh yes. Aye. Oh you could talk to mother - better - better than me father you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother show affection? Did she show that she was fond of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh aye, she was always a good mother. Well they were a good mother and father and all as far as that goes, I mean, me - me dad were a bit rougher than me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 If you'd had any worries could you have shared them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, could go and tell her if - if there were - some 'at weren't right. Oh aye, always take your troubles home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was your father easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 He weren't in - sometimes - better than others you know. But - we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You went to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your father show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Not a - not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 If you had any worries could you share them with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - to tell you 
the truth I never had any - worries big enough to take to him. We don't hardly dare. Aye. You know what I mean. He wanted you - he was strict, you know what I mean, and he - if you'd been into any mischief at all and got into any trouble - you'd sooner Bo
bby catch you than him. Aye. I would. In my young days. I didn't bother about policemen, but - I bothered if me dad caught me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What would have happened if he had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh dear, he used to get that belt and he - he didn't know when to leave off. But t
hat's why I never took no trouble home. None of family. No, girls nor boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would the girls have got the belt as well or just the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh yes, it was used on them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 For what sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 If they were - if they were - long over the wheel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What does that mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well, sometimes - if a neighbour come and said anything about you. He'd give you a good hiding. But if you - if you'd really been on at something and he'd caught you and he'd told you to go an errand and you stopped p
laying or anything of that, she - such as that - you'd be for it. If you were supposed to be going an errand and you stopped playing balls or - or football or anything like that with the other lads and he had - bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would this have been on your bare behind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no, he don't bother where - where it were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How many would you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh - me dad - he'd leave off when he left off. He were too strict. But mind you can understand it with all that family couldn't you, you see what I mean. But he did, he kept 'em right, he kept us -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of things was he very strict about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well anything, if you'd - if you - if he had heard talk of you fetching apple out of somebody's garden or anything of that you see, all - bits as that. But you 
never went - done what they do now. I'm sure we'd have got murdered. If we'd have done what some of the lads does today. We should have been murdered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well just ordinary. They was your moth
er and father. Well they just - respect - respected them - you respect them as mother and father, aye. They just wanted you to behave yourself in the ordinary way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you argue with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well we got - we got as we could argue with me father
, but in his younger days we couldn't. When we were young. We did later - in later life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, always used to - bring you up to - hang together and tha
t - but they don't always hang together. Not - not the same as they were brought up early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they - teach you? Oh yes. Yes, wanted you to stick up for yourself but not to - to 
get - get into - you know, doing - doing wrong or nothing like that. They let you stand on your own feet. If anybody - me dad's say, go and - you're big enough go bash his head and go and have go, he said, when you came back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - me mother especially hoped us - see we'd been brought up - as Christians and - always look after that side of things. My mother and father lived -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, cleanliness. Aye. Cleanliness and - and truthfulness. That were the - two main objects.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh - wouldn't let you swear. In fact we never - with not being - heard it and no
t - we - we never did bother swearing much, you know what I mean, we - we didn't - didn't want to try.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well sometimes we were, it all depends - what conversation was of course. The - we could - all join in together. Often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You weren't kept down in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. Oh we weren't actually kept down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You told me how your father punished you, what about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh mother didn't let you do as you liked.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How would she have dealt with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 She'd give you a bit of a - clip or two. If you - if you'd gone a bit too far. She'd pull you up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of things would she punish you for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well she - she'd thought you'd broke something and it was in a bit - 
in temper or anything like that you'd get a good hiding. You dropped a saucer or anything what you're wiping or anything, and she thought you'd done it 'cos you didn't like job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So how often did she punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh not often. It were something unusual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How often did your father punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - I've known him to give me a right good hiding, don't know - I know that that's for. If I've been out - and he's fancied I've been - a bit - on anything that as he won't like, give you a clink l
ike that, he says, you know what that's for. Ten watch you, see if you're guilty. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you give yourself away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No. No. But I mean that's how he were. He rattled first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, only - only for play - only for playing football on a Sunday. Aye, that were - that were - that - that were my biggest hiding I got.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - we'd been to Sunday school, and we was - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 we\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  found a field where we thought nob
ody else could find us in this field. I should be about - nine or ten years of age. So - we had - we was thinking we had got this field to ourselves, we - we set about it proper. We }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 chose}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  a side and - put us clothes down. And me dad had got wi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 nd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 on us. So,
 he come. I'll tell you where it were, it were straight opposite where they built that - Longbow, and you went up that hill and then there were a level piece and then you went down a hill that side. So they couldn't see it off of none of the roads. And me
 dad come walking up one of those. Yes. That were it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
He said - I - I - shot - shot off you know, so he followed me and when he got that - when he got home I was back in. I said, what's the matter, to me dad. I've been playing foot
ball. Ooh, she said, you'll catch it when he comes in. I said, aye. Said, here he comes. And off comes his belt. Bangs me upstairs. Then - finished me meals that day. And - a good hiding - get a good hiding at it. Aye. That were - that job.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How bruised were you after this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - you got marks on you. But not actually bruised. It's that shop on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Front Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and I had ha'penny. Ha'penny on me. So I said, Mrs Clay, them bowlers sixpence ha'penny aren't they? She said, yes my lad. I said, do you th
ink I could get one if I brought you a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487  ha\rquote penny }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 every week 'til I've paid for it? She sa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
d, of course you can. So I - I took a ha'penny every week, that was all I could guarantee her getting but I sometimes used to get another copper - somewhere else like.
 But I could guarantee I'd get this ha'penny. So I took her this 'ere ha'penny, that was thirteen week, twelve - twelve bar that as I - give her - give her the ha'penny. So I said, that's it then Mr Clay, then, I've paid for it. She says, aye, you've paid
 
it lad. Give me bowler and I went home - proud as peacock. And when I got to - Derrymount turn there I could see me father in garden, I said, dad look what I've got. He - do you know what he said to me. He said, you've got more money than sense. He says, 
you've got more money than sense.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Bringing you up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh me mother played biggest part. Yes. Oh aye, mother played biggest part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - it were a bit but not much,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Give you - little - perhaps a bit of something new, new - new scarf or a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}new jersey{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, a me pair of socks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Clothing usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Bit - aye. Clothing or - it was pretty near always clothes, some clothing. It was same as Christmas, you only - you generally got bit of clothing or - apple or orange or - new penny or something l
ike in your stocking. There were no big toys, no toys or any of that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would you have anything special to eat on birthdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no, don't think we had any special - any special birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you remember anything special you did with your father and mother together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well used to call it - have a Christmas dinner but there were now - special about anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No. No, we never had no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We - the first music we had we - was out of a gramophone, one of 'em - one on 'em played a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What stage would this have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh I've forgot when it would be. But I know it were old fashioned and it were wh
at - what we used to call - the records were like - jam jars shape.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Rolls were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Used to fit 'em on and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 This was when you were a schoolboy was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, when - when I was young, I forget which -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of tunes did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They were all old fashioned, I can't remember 'em now. Oh - we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Ah me dad used to play us at cards and - dominoes. Ludo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were there any books in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, a few books. Very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you take newspapers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We took - we - they took one - one newspaper a week, that were ha'penny Post Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there something special about the Saturday Post?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, no, I don't think so. That were the - that w
as special for mother and father more than anything, but I never - can always they used to call and fetch a Post Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they get any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well there were church monthly. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Me dad - did very little reading, same as I say, what bit of reading he learnt were what mother learnt him. But he got as he could read newspaper a bit - in his later life, but apart from that he read - read nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember your parents reading aloud to you or each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother read the paper to your father to begin with or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well it were perhaps we'd gone to bed but - we - I - never seen 'em reading - never see 'em sit reading to one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 That girl. Aye. Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How old would you have been then? You would have been quite young wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I was young. I can remember funeral though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who went to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They carrie
d - they carried her - to the - to the church yard. I've forgot who followed. Whether I did or not I've forgot. But I know they had ask - after - ours was quite a long yard, and then they was carrying her to - churchyard, the old churchyard. And then a li
t
tle round table, bottom of our - to rest her on while they - suppose they bury her and didn't have to stand holding her, that's how they worked it at that - that time anyway. Anyone as died up there that time they carried. See they carried 'em - to the ch
urchyard. Aye, there were no - no hearses. Had no hearse, no cabs. I forgot how old I was then but - I should be - very young. Young lad, very young lad, anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember whether people wore mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well they were black. Aye, oh
, they used to wear black. Oh aye, they all - all had a black tie or a black bow or a - some - some kind of black, or black arm or some 'at at that time of day, pretty near everybody - funerals, they had more black then than they do now you know. Oh aye. 
There was a black suit for - them as could afford 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours, did you ever go on special sort of visits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Or to relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - no not a deal. Very little of that. Very little visiting anytime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well I - I were taken when - when I were a lad to buy me clothes and - and me shoes. Then when we got old enough we used to - take ourselves you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were taken who took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Mother. Mother always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you ever go out just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
We used to go - up garden with him and - and little walks round - country walks a bit but not - to go anywhere else. Never went to seaside or none of them places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember any outings with your parents on Bank Holidays for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I never remember any at all but - I know I went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}
Wales{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - on - holiday. Easter or Whitsuntide or - August - holiday Monday. I got a job wheeling out - I were a school lad, but I got a job wheeling up - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Stamford Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. They went to Trentbridge. And he - he'd got about - five or six of 'em with him. So they went - I - it were one of me sisters told me about this like, her next younger. She says, go down, she says, took us in to buy a cup of tea and - a cak
e, and it - when it - when he - he reckoned up he says, missus, that'll be so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you ever go to Trentbridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I never went - never went with him in me life. No, nowhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you ever go anywhere on a treat like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So did you ever go away on a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 The only time that - first time that I seen side - seen seaside it were a - when we went with a choir outing. On a church choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I should be about twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Where did you get to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Sutton-on-Sea they went. That were place here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was the tide in or out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - we were pretty near all day so I should say - it'd be in and out and all while we were there. I know we spent most of us money on ponies, 
what bit of money we got and it weren't very little - very much at that time. That's we spent all us money in - what bit we'd saved and collected together to go away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, pretty near alwa
ys at - at gardens. Helping dig or - set and one thing and another. 'Til we - 'til we got a bit older. Then we - we used to do - go about - bit - bit of footballing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well Sundays we used to go to station -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You had clean clothes didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh aye, we had - we always had our Sunday suits. Oh yes. We always got that privilege. Of course when we'd done with 'em on Sundays we never seen 'em again all week. But it were there though, I don't mean - they went in pawn shop,
 but we never - weren't allowed to wear 'em only on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did Sunday go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well Sunday we - we just went to church about three times a day. Used to go at Sunday school in the morning, I - I think it were half past nine if I remember right 
we used to be there. Then I was in choir. And then - then - then there'd be Sunday school in afternoon. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 14}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 
30}}}Half past two{\*\xmlclose}. Then it were choir again - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past six{\*\xmlclose}
. That's how my Sundays went. And that time as I tell you - when you go to football were between 
- coming out Sunday school and him catching us, you see. You see, we - we - that's what made us try to pinch an hour. 'Cos the - the time was pretty well occupied. We didn't have as much as freedom as some lads you know. I didn't anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Your parents thought it was wrong to play football on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they think it was wrong to work or play otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 It were - it was only work only necessary - only necessaries. Necessary work. Wouldn't let you go - she wouldn't let you go an
d work on a - same I had a - done that day weeds, weren't allowed go - on that, wouldn't let you go on that - on that - on that. No. Not Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would she have done anything like knitting on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - in - in the majority, no, she never d
one no knitting, she - she often had to do a bit of - what she called borrow, stitch a button on or something of that for anybody, that were only -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 If it was necessary it was all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh - it was necessary in some cases where - a child had got
 a button off she'd put it on again, sew it on sort of business but - not to - to make a regular practice of making on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, mother did. Dad didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Which church was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Arnold{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 St Mary's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How often did your mother go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well as often as she could really. But it wasn't every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. There were - first outing - first Sunday school outing I c
an remember went to Holly Lodge. Had a - what they call a brake ride. A - horse and brake, to Holly Lodge, just - towards Bar - the other side of Barnstall here, had a tea and then a - bit of a play and - come back. That were your - Sunday school outing. 
Then you got a - a bit on Whit Tuesday you know. Used to have a tea and then go and play in one of fields. In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Ascot{\*\xmlclose}
 field up - Northwood End then. That field there, that one just below where tip - aye. Aye, that's it, that's the one. As we played in, after the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 next}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  Tuesday tea. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were the Whit walks going on in your day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh aye. We never took part in at that time of day though. We - we used to go watch-look - watching, but - the church didn't walk. Never walked 'til - quite recently - starte
d walking, aye. Aye, quite recently, the church - church never walked in our in my young days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You were in the choir weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, I were in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have any other treats as a choir? Did you get a choir outing every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Wel
l I - I forgot, I don't think - it weren't every year, but we had one or two - outings. One or two different outings. And then you see - get a bit of a choir - choir supper round about Christmastime or something like that, I - I just forget how - how we w
ent - on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did the church run any temperance clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Band of Hope or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, had a Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you a member or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I - that sister, Mary, she was a member there. One or two of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 
youngsters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  - I believe it started about that time, started that Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Only Bible Class. When we - when we got older we - we went Bible Class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was grace said at meals in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 At ho
me? No, I'll show you - a slice of that - and he says - he says, I'll tell you what lad, he says - call in tomorrow afternoon, he says, I'm going down in pit in the morning I'll see what I can fix you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Just left school, a
bout thirteen and a half. Or four - nearly fourteen. So - when he comes out of office - who should put his lamp in, put it through a window you know where - like that office you know, than - than me dad. So - what do you think you're doing up here? Been s
e
eing mister in there. What for he says? Have you been asking for a job? I said, aye. What's he said to you? I said, he's told me to come up tomorrow and he's going to fix me. So he said, I'll fix you if you're not off home, he said, I'll kill you. So - he
 
says - oh, he says, come here, I want you. Of course when your dad tell you to come here you've got to go, there's no saying, I - I'm off, I'm - you know, same it is now, run away, when he says, come here - oh, he says, I'll go in with you. So he goes wal
king in. Now Mister - call him his name, I've forgot his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 name}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 though but I - I've got the idea his name was Robbins. Now Mr - what about this lad? Me dad's name was Sam you know. So he says, well what about him Sam, he says, you've just been in here. I says
, I have. He says, I'm going to fix him up tomorrow, he says, I'm going down pit down tomorrow. He dad says, aye - if I put me hand in me pock - pocket and gave you half a sovereign or to like that you'd fix him up today wouldn't you? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 He}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  turned round to me and said, if you're coming here again, he says, you'll know what you'll get. Make haste off home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 He was very against you going down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 He did everything to stop me. See? None of boys had been to pit, none of the other lads - before. But you see 
he never got me a job anywhere. I had to battle for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you look for other jobs first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
I'd been round factories and everywhere but you - you'd got to be born in a factory to get on at that time of day, in a factory, well especially Allum
 and Solley's. Your Dad had got to be there or somebody. You'd got to be born - same as I say, born in it. It was pretty near same on all of 'm. Only on land. You couldn't go on land, you had to go at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning 'til {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 
18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night, f
or tenpence. Or they used to give you a shilling. So, anyway - I came along and you see - I started buying - bits and bobs at Tom Andrews, onions and radishes and - when red cabbage were in going round selling 'em. Earning money that road. And I were earn
ing more money than going to work. Aye. I were buying these - these so I didn't bother after a job for a while you know. Then I got a bit fed up. Then I went and got a job at Sheerwood - laundry. I were there about two - bit over two year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 Aye. So - one - one - Thursday I think it was, we never used to have to go out - 'til seven o'clock at night Thursday on a journey, delivering. It weren't ready for us you see. So we got that afternoon free. And I got - I'd got a bike then.
 On that bike and went - went to Gedling - and got a job.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Gedling pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You were different from father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So - I daresn't tell him when I got home. No. That went on 'til Sunday teatime. Mother says - you're taking your time, W
alter, aren't you? Well, I said, I'm not in no hurry. I wanted tell 'em and I didn't know how to bring it out you know. So she says - aren't you moving yet? Aye, I'll be over in a minute or two. She says, what's this then? I said, well I shall want some d
i
fferent clothing to work in in morning. So she says, why, aren't them good enough, Aye, I said, they're too good. 'Cos you used to - go in anything - any old things to pit 'cos you used to - you was at work, and you - and in the - latter part of time we -
 
got we could change at the bath you know. We couldn't then. So I said, no, they're too good. So she said, why? How do you mean to good? I says, well, I'm going to pit. I said, I'm going early and all. And me dad sit in that same position as I sit here and
 
I sat over there. He said - do as you like. I've stopped you once. I thought - I thought to myself, I'm winning. Do as you like, he said, I've stopped you once. So that were it. But I went down all right so they let next lad go. 'Cos it were only place wh
ere they could earn a bit of - money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But your father had stopped the older ones going down or hadn't they wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They hadn't wanted. They never offered you see, but he - he never took 'em. Never took none of 'em. Then when I went on me own h
e let me go. You see. Well - he - he - I went on me own this, but he stopped me there. When I'd just left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But you were two years older by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Ah, bit over two. About three - three years by then I think when I went down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What happened the first day you went down, how do you start learning, do you get attached to an older miner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh - aye. If you start as a young - younger boy and I - I were a bit older than some of 'em what start, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You'd be about fifteen would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
I - I believe I - fourteen - fifteen, sixteen, I were nearly seventeen. And nearly - and really like a young man you see then. To what some of these lads were when they start at fourteen you know. Well I - they put me on a - driving a - one of the
se - engines - that - nearly in pit bottom for a bit. So - a chap come to me and showed me how to - how to - start it and stop it and - what way to wheel and - and how to go on a bit. Then something happened, they fetched him away. So he had to - go and g
et yourself then. So you went on as usual.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 This was driving the trucks was it down below?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Driving - what they called - rope haulage. The - the rope used to - run round and - there was them tubs on and - pull 'em up and take the empties - back in
 to work again. I was driving that. Oh after I done that for quite - quite a while, then I went up the - they said, you'd better go up road a bit. So I started going up loaded with a couple of ponies and - one thing and another 'til I - they said I'd bett
e
r start on coalface, when I got about - twenty. I started on coalface and stopped on coalface, after then. But - you see - I were a young boy - he'd perhaps have a ld with him a bit older than him, half a shift - to start him off, or a shift, one day, you
 
see, to learn him - ins and out of ganging. What they called ganging. Pony driving. Aye, that's how they used to learn. But you know the - before I left pit - I got me arm broke in 1954. Aye. So - there was a job going at Bestwood - training boys. So I we
nt to - the manager Mr Johnson. I said, Mr Johnson, I want a job under you. He said, if you want a job under me, well he says you can have one if }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 gaffer'll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  let you. He says, I don't want to stand in your road. Here we are. So I says, well I'll go and see th
e gaffer then. So I got job. Well, what I were after - the only job I could get was two pound - pension to. You see, so him as what I were working under says to me, said, well he said, tell me you've been after a job on - on gallery wall. I says, aye. But
 
I was interested in the money more - more than what I was in job. So - he says, well you'll be all right, he says, you ought to get nine pound a week there. That - that'd be like round about 19 - fifty - aye, '55. But I'd only got until - 'til '59. So he 
b
ooked me all up and I got few - and I get this 'ere balance. But what I were referring to - difference in training - boys from that day to now. You'd five lads - and you learn 'em every job there were you see, they're with you three month. And then they g
o
 to - they come to you one week and another set - set - comes to you that week well that - week when they change they go - they go to a school at Uphall. Learn all the - schoolwork and things, everything. Have - three months - three months - between 'em l
ike. But you've got 'em like what you call three months, if you aint got one set you've the other. And you learn 'em every job there is in pit. Packing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What was your title when you were teaching them, did you have a special name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I was called a - training instructor. That were me job. Training instructor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were twenty how was the coal getting arranged, did you have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 
butties}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  or something? Were you working as a team always?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh yes, yes, there was maybe about - three and - three a
nd four of you together. Sometimes a bit more, sometimes seven - as many as seven. But mostly -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was one man in charge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 charge man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 . Or what they called butty. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did the butty get paid and share it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When I first st
arted - on coalface, the butty paid you a day's wage. And he had what were left. Well then it come as a throw in. What they call throw in. That means if you'd earnt ten pounds, the three on you would share it up. If you'd been your time as - as pits made,
 you shared up a piece - between you. That's three pound odd a piece. But if - and then - he had what they call }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 charge man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 money. Perhaps it'd be about two shilling a day. More than other men - the other two you see, it - it'd be what you call }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 charge man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  mo
ney then. But that were a - the butty system. Wouldn't matter if you'd earnt - forty pound - he'd only give you your day's wage. Or less if he could get away with it. But you know at that time of day they used to - pay same as paying the rent man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, butty did. To keep his job. Because I proved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did that happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
I proved it with - when I was about - been in coal - on coalface about - four - about four year, one of the men as were - buttying - says to me, they used to -
 take a great load down like that and set a stall off there and that cut this lower down off in time. And - you see, then - setting one out there then go further and set another out. And then when they've got all - all coal had gone from there they used t
o
 move up. Clear the field you see, that's how they worked it. Well when we - they were going to set this - this one out here, he said, you know when we've set this one out here Walt, he said, shall you turn in with me? He meant join him. Him on one shift,
 me on another you see. So I says, no, I said, I'm all right. It were all for him then. It'd all cleared up do you see. I said, I don't want - I don't want buttying. I don't want it. He says, buttying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487  is}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  finishing. He said, it - no, it was throw in - it was throw in then, that were it. I said, I don't want to be a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 charge man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
, I says - he says, well this is the throw in systems - finishing he says, it'll be buttying in a bit again, he says, you'll see. 'Cos I - smelt it. In fact I'd wise to - wire it up. So h
e says, what do you say? I said, well I'll consider it. And I turned in with - and I maintained I got my job on me merits. See what I mean? So - when we'd had it a while the first one used to come - Friday - specially. And he'd rap on your - with his - yo
u
 had a plate - tin - steel plate what you spin - spin it around and guide it under your rails you know. And he used to come with his stick - tapping like that. And I used to ignore him. Guv'nor wanted so much. Gaffers wanted so much. When we were at the p
i
t bottom there was tub out - what they call a tub out. It were bad coal you'd sent. So I says to gaffer - I says, how do you know what's in that tub? I says, it's - they're full. I said, tops all right ain't it. Aye, he says, but there's bad inside. I sai
d
, well, I said, let's have it up pit and turned over and see. I said, if you're not satisfied clear off. See, that's how it was - how we would do. See, you'd not - you - you got - you couldn't - pass no evidence, you'd got no proper evidence you see. If h
e
 said it were a bad 'un it were a bad 'un. So - it went on a while and do you know what happened, what purpose - the purpose it - purpose the - shove us out. These men as were in here - used to - travel to there. Them men as were in here traveled there, t
hey made them come to here and then come to a close down, fetched you out on it. See? That's 'cos they wouldn't - and the worse reason 'cos you wouldn't pay your rent.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And how much were they expecting, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh - as much as they could get
 hold of. They don't bother if you get a lot. At that time of day you know, used to get - give 'em an orange with a golden quid in. You - when they come round there's orange in my jacket pocket. Used to go and - fetch it out for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you taught to say prayers at night at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We was when we was very young but they didn't - after we got at bit older we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. He'd no interest in politics. Very little anyway, only just went and vote I - I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well at that time of day it were Liberal. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you know why he was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I think the - they'd a bit better - watched over in a way of speaking did Liberals than what they did with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 Tories}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 . They got the eight hour act through you know, the - that's one thing - in their favour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, she'd no interest in politics. Well I think it were same as me dad's.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you know why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In a little way like. Well same purpose of course, she thought it were better for the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember your father or mother voting in a general election before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Before - oh yes. Oh aye, I can remember 'em voting before then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They both voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh I was - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they both vote for the Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I should be twenty-five then, I - I can well remember then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 As far as you know they would both vote for the Liberal party would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 As far as I knew, I - what bit they did say. Sounded as if they - held with Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employ
ers, do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure, to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh no. Don't think so. Can't think of anything like that. It were just a matter of - them being - a little bit better looked after at work - as regards that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was your father a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. No, never a member.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You don't remember him working for one of the parties at an election then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did either of your parents take part in any political activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You said they weren't very interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, it were just a matter of voting I expect. They went and cast their vote some - in fact I don't think sometimes they bothered.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well they were pretty near always occupied. Me dad's got plenty of - work on and me mother and all. They didn't have much - time for - making - aye, they didn't have much time for anything bar - some interest as regards work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they ever do anything else but work in one way or another:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I don't know of any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Only if one of the neighbours were ill or anything like that. She would do - help a neighbour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh no. I can never remember her going out. Only when there was a - wedding, one of - wedding or anything like that but - but - it had got to be an occasion like that, for her to be out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - when he was on day shift he was home round about five o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And how many evenings would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 He'd spend about all of 'em after he - after he'd finished his - his - diff
erent jobs like, looking after - if it were light - like for gardening or anything like that, a light night. An hour or so. But of course - always at home after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he go to any pubs or clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh he - bit of a member at Liberal club. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he go regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, it were very occasional.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could women go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh - oh no, not then. No. Mother wasn't - mother - mother never went anywhere for a drink. Never.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Sport? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he attend the races ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. No, no, I can never remember him going to any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They did have a point-to-point some - somewhere - round about Woodborough, at that - in
 that time of day. I never remember him bothering though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well at that time there was that penny bank - what Mr Truman had, the Vicar. They belonged that a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did that work, the Vicar ran it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
The Vicar run it up, at back of police station there. What they call penny bank. That was a - what the bit of savings they were - used to go to. That was all. There wasn't no other bank in Arnold. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they belong to a boot club do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Sick clubs? He belonged - he belonged to a - a Lodge as run a sick club, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 
Hollywood}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  Lodge. Thorneywood. Thorneywood Lodge. Well we all belonged it as we got a - as we got older like
. Used to - get ten shillings if you're off work - for ten - for ten week. And then you got to go a year before you'd benefit again you see, that's how it worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did that pay for the doctor or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No, well - we had what they call - that - 
when it come about we had what they called family doctor. But whether it were in my very young days or not I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How much did you have to pay a week for the doctor then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I've just forgot it actually I think it was - only a few coppers. Or one copper if anything for children. Very little anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Funeral clubs or anything, burial clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I don't think so. Not as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh we all got on pretty - pretty well as you 
might say, we perhaps little tiffs odd times but - we never bore any malice, it was soon over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there any one of your family that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I - I don't think there were any exceptions. Think they were - they were al
l - think they were all alike. No, don't think there was any - oh no, don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When I was a boy? Well, any neighbours round about home like. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 
Knights' children and - well - first one neighbour and then another you know at that time, you could leave any time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
I mean - you might have a family live at bottom - bottom of road there, six - six, seven weeks then they'd be gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 As often as that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Why did they move so frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I - I don't know. In some cases - perhaps it were - through - the father left a job or - anything of that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you play with neighbours more than your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - them as were round about us own age, we - of course as they got older they - dropped out, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well there were no playing fields. We used to - play in that field what is a playing field now, on Derrymount, back of the church there. 'Til we got run out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Why did you get run out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 'Cos it were a field you see, it was a - factory field. Aye. And - then we had to play in lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Which lane was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 That Churchmore Lane is now. It was called Derrymount then, called Derrymount. Bottom - we used to call it botto
m lane and top lane, but it were - it had got no name. And then they named it Churchmore Lane. As - as got up to - to - more town you know, that's - that's the Churchmore Lane. Then bottom lane - come up from Church Lane - and the little short lane where 
they met - well - our playing in that - where recreation ground is now, a Mr Nee}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15033000\charrsid9707487 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
ham had the field, the greengrocer up - High Street. Of course we shot off sooner than let him catch us. We left us jackets. When I gets home me dad says, where's your jacket? I said, Mr Needham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 s took it. And I was getting on then, I should be about - twelve or thirteen years of age. He said, you're going round to Mr Nee}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 ham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
s then and fetch it. So - I went and - Mr Needham's shop, it were - where - Smiths barber now, at bottom
 of Chapel Lane. Mrs was in the shop so she said, yes my boy. Or some words similar to that. I said, I've come for me jacket please. She says, your jacket? I said, aye, Mr Needham took 'em out field. So he come and - threatened to - threatened me like wit
h this that and - so I said, well it don't matter what you do I've got to take my jacket home. I get - I get - got him on to give me the other lads. And that were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Brimley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  - Bramley lad up - there, but we got us jackets all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Pretty well football. And - tin lurky. Duck stone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What's duck stone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You had to set a brick up and put a - stone -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Ducks and drakes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, bit - big stone on top and then - then knock it off and then run. Them as got caught t
hey were on. They were on that. That were duck stone. Oh we used to have to play any game but we never - never got nothing that cost you money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You had another name for stick and goose too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Billet. Stick and billet. Aye. Stick and billet used - 
we'd have to be careful when we were playing - playing with that or - there'd be broken windows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well we were, yes, you know, not to the extreme.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, we had - we had good neighbours like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents ever discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No, they didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you belong to any youth organisations, were there any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I don't think there
 was any. Not 'til we got - that were the first organisation in that Bible Class that I - there was a Band of Hope started somewhere about that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you belong to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No, me sisters - joined it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were still at school did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - only helping in garden. None on me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you enjoy helping in the garden or did you just feel you had to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I used to enjoy it but I still had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But you did enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, I didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No, they'd got plenty of - we'd got pet rabbits and that but - me dad used to keep 'em for - killing. Them - white - what did they used to call 'em, white - I forget name now. Forgot the names what they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you tell me that bit again about what you used for a football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well sometimes the ball was made of part of those stocking tops, and tied up - tided up together with thin string you know and made a ball of it. So that were - we had to make that fo
r us ball and - couldn't buy one. And when we played cricket it were a just a wooden paling and a - a wooden ball of the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 It was a bit dangerous wasn't it, did anyone ever get hurt?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, used to - at time but not any - severity to it though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you collect anything as a hobby when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. No, we never made no collections or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, we used to walk. Rambling a bit, what we called rambling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you get far?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Sometimes got as far as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6236194\charrsid9707487 Causey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  or - Bramley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you go bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have bicycles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, I had a bicycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 At what sort of age did you get a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of age were you when you got a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - such - such as I got - it were one of me brother's - worn out, and there was no tyres on. And no bell. And I don't think any mudguards. And I come riding down - Butts as we called it then, that's - on Re
dhill - Redhill Road - with - got up to - going to Redhill - and policeman was at bottom and - and - we had - I'd got no brakes. So I used to have to - run into the hedge to stop myself. So - anyway - his name were Bobby Books, I do know that. Biggish bro
a
d - Bobby you know. And he's after making a bit of fun with me like, he says, hey up, where's your bell? It's coming down the hill with cobbles on as big as - boulders you know, them - it were just - just - just making more - more noise than a steam engin
e - steam roller. Aye, so - where's your bell? So that were - that were Bobby. Aye, that were the bike as I learnt to ride on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You still ride don't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye. I've rode it ever since. I went to work for - all time on - in my working life. Aye.
 Very near all the time anyway, if it was very bad weather - it had got to be bad weather for me to go on bus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who did you do these things like rambling and bicycling with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well with me own chaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Just play football a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you play proper football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Aye, not - not with a League. Not with League football. But they - they first started a team of Arnold St - Arnold Sunday school. And that run - I've got a photo on it somewhere, in there somewh
ere. That run for - for about two seasons. Then we made another one up - forgot what they called that. But that was before - before St Mary's got going. Aye. And we played on - that - ground at back of - back of Cross Keys. Aye, they was round there then.
 Played there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Theatre? We used to go to - down to the Hippodrome odd time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were still a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No. After I started work. After I started work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you go to concerts in Arnold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I can never remember going to any - oh, or very few anyway, but I - I don't remember going to any - concerts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Music halls as a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 There was no music halls - in Arnold. We used to - we used to get odd - odd show come onto that croft. Different - times, acting - k

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they do this in a tent or in the open air?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 It were a tent. You'd have factory lads and that on strike and - they'd all be tramping down cobble streets of Manchester.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Clog dances?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, they got the - t
he dolls to represent lad - lads running down street you know. Used to charge us two or three coppers to go in. Then they used to - act different - different men or - Maria Martin's Red Barn and one thing and another. And him as got made it first - he wer
e
 first out like so they were first down to jockey for a pint. And one time there was - they were - they'd pulled blind - blind down and he started getting up and he got that - he got - muddled with blind, he pulled it up again and he were just getting up,
 he - he was supposed to be - he dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you ever go to the cinema while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No, there weren't no cinemas. The first cinema as come - started where I just tell you we were playing football. As I can remember coming in Arno
ld. And the man as - used to be shouting and taking tickets - you could stand at the top the arch see, on the Arch Bridge and hear him shouting. This way, this way. You could hear his voice right up there. Well when we were - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 oldish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  - lads it - it - might 
be - perhaps you'd be - round about fourteen. And - he used to start taking pennies off of these lads, oh his own you see, and it were tuppence - or - else threepence to go fetch your ticket. But they rumbled it. Yes, they rumbled us. That man that Ernie,
 he did that for a good while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were a schoolboy did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No, we never got no pocket money to go to school - to school. The only pocket money I - same as I told you - as I can guarantee were a ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You got it every week didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Yes. I could guarantee getting that. That's why I went and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 paid}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  that bowler up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you weren't saving up what did you spend your money on ordinarily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - few }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 toffees}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  or - aniseed balls or anything like that, there weren't very much variation then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Mostly sweets was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Aye. If we got - we could get - either - beg a few apples or go and scrump 'em from somewhere handy. That time of day. They didn't used to say nothing to you. You went and picked one up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 The word's scrumping isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Aye, scrumping, it was called scrumping - then. You didn't - you didn't used to - didn't used to call it pinching. When - some on 'em - they'd throw you one or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house and family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. The only - the only -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - there were more - from - from my memory there were mostly one older sister to - to 
take - take it on a bit. Or - or all - all lads had to do the - like - you see when there were no sisters, you see. Where I dropped - there were four lads - followed each other. So it left - left - the - the sisters had - had gone. One died and the other 
got married. What were older than me. So it made it as lads had to take - more - that girls what would - what would have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember what happened when one of your younger brothers or sisters was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I don't remember much about bi
rths. I - my - my mother in bed and - we got another - extra come and that - that were about as much as you got to know about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But you and the others would have helped in the house, no aunt would have come or anything like that, if your mother wa
s confined to bed with a baby or anything like that would any other relation have come to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I never remember 'em - I never remember none of 'em coming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well, me dad's - family, brothers and sisters lived - round about Arnold like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How much did you see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh very little unless we went - just called odd times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I don't think they had - had many as what you call friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Not friends at all, were they too busy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I - aye, they were always busy enough with their own family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would your mother have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. Don't think she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So were any ever invited to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Anybody invited? Oh no. No, they never - they never had -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did any call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
They used to - odd times that was all. Their - like the sister and - mother's brother in-law and sister-in-law, they used to call odd time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But these were actual relations weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Oh aye, relations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When did relations call in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they come for any special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I think it'd be when they were - perhaps having a walk round and - just drop in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was Arnold }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Wakes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  a special family occasion, did people come back for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well it were a bit of - it were a bit of a - occasion but it - it weren't much recognized at hour house. No. We perhaps got a extra ha'penny or - to spend or penny you know what I mean - that - that were about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did neighbours ever call round without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Neighbours? Not unless they come for - some - errand or business or anything like that. Very - very little as come into - gossip like.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I don't think they went out a deal. As I said they were pretty well occupied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did
 when they got together with their friends or neighbours or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh I don't think they - was together long enough to make any amusement. Just have a bit of a talk and - that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you given lessons by one of your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Lessons? No. No, we had no lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
To tell you the truth I don't know, I think I must have been four - four or five, I think I was about that - somewhere about that age when I went.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Which school did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Calverton Road. That same school as is there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Nine o'clock in morning we used to go in school. Come out at twelve. Back again at two - 'til four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Even when you were four or five you did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, it were - all time were - were at that school that was routine - as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of school was it, was it a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Yes, it were a chur
ch - yes, it was church school - that. Used to have a vicar come every - Monday. Give us a - bit of a lecture. On - on the Bible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How long did it take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Not many minutes. Across that - across that churchyard it weren't many minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 One another. One another, two of us. Or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you go home for your midday meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh there was no - no school meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did you think if school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well I - weren't - a good scholar or nothing of that but I never used to detest it. I used to - used to take it in its stride. But you see I lost a lot of time after - after I got a start at school I - I just forget how 
old I was, I was struck down with typhoid fever.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Roughly how old would you have been, do you know at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I should think six. Seven. It - put me back. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you off school for months and months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, because had to stop - when on
e got - I had to stop - off school, when - when I was all right in a way of speaking. Then - then when - when I got better I had to stop at home with another left in. See it started with me father. Aye, and then it went - through - I forget how - just exa
ctly how many there was but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Does anyone know where he got it from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
I know at least there were five of us. Well I - we always thought - that he was a bit off - colour and kept going to work, and he were coming home and in them barracks on Redhil
l - I don't know whether you - whether you know where I mean but they used to call 'em barracks then. There's only the front row left now. And they're ready for pulling down, they're emptying. They're the first row past church - past chapel. Straight oppo
s
ite Redhill Road you know. And that - straight off it - that road - that walk leads you up to Bestwood - wood. That's the barrack - that were the barracks. And they were all - at that time they were all - there was about four - three or four years - full 
o
f houses. Aye. And these - emptying - men was emptying and he come by. And felt it get hold on him. The smell like. And that - that's - he struck - took bad with this typhoid. And then it went through - I believe there were five of us - beside me dad. As 
-
 as had it. I know me brother John and - Arthur, me - and then - I've forgot - I know - I know that - there were either four - four of me - besides me dad or five. And me mother nursed us all through it. Me mother nursed us all through it. The only help w
e
 got was a - what they call a district nurse used to come and wash us. And she weren't in the house - well perhaps best part of half an hour. And then me dad's sister sent - a woman up - to help me mother do a bit of housework. Help with that. One of me d
a
d's sisters. Paid her. She sent her like. And paid her two or three coppers, well it wouldn't be a lot of - lot of money at that time of day. Paid her to come and - do a bit for me mother. Do a bit of housework. And we had no help for - as regards money n
or not. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How long was your father off work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well he was off - he was off quite a while. I don't - I couldn't say how - how long he were off but I know - when I was getting better - I can remember this myself - he held me up - in front of a 
mirror, not quite so big at that pane there, and he says, who's that? I said, its Jack Cyclop that is, I says, I'm not going about Jack }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Cyclop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 , I want some tapioca pudding. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You were feeling a bit hungry then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, they clam you. Over that 
job they clam it out of you you see, well you know - you know - aye. And - and - and when you started getting better you could eat - you could eat - anything. You know, I were - bit of a lover of tapioca pudding so I said it would be tapioca pudding.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I expect you were too young then to know how the family managed when your father wasn't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh I don't know how - how we did manage I tell you. I know one or two things got neglected a bit. Aye. In bedrooms and that. I do know that from me own memory. And I - I know they wouldn't have -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You don't know how they managed for money at that time do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh - a bit of - well, it were a lump of a scrap. I know - we were - we had our - where bedrooms were - with me mother being so - too busy, 
you know, and it - had to leave that myself. She was too busy. Then they got that - that - that daughter got back at time. That was on her back. She used to have to take her down to the hospital. Me mother had one of them three wheel - chair a sit so happ
ened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You took her all the way from here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Had to wheel her backward and forwards. Back and forwards to Nottingham. To the general hospital in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Up that hill as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were at school then did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh same as I say, used to take it in its stride, I never used - I didn't do - I didn't dislike and I didn't have a liking, I - just - went ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - they were all - I'd got no special 
- teacher or no - no interest in teacher, I used to take them see and - they were teacher and that were it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, not at that time. Not as I know to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What about things like manners
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Only Arnold Ellis. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Arnold}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  Ellis, he - I can remember him saying, we can't make you a bishop.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was he a teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So what did he think he was going to make you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, I can't make you a bishop. That were at - this school do
wn - what's ready for being pulled down now. On Front Street. What did they used to call it, that - no, I've forgot name - used to call it - British. British school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you change schools then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 That was the only two schools I went to. Calverton Road and British.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Why did you change schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
You had to change when you got older. And - last - last two years down there. Be about - last - last year - last two year I think it was that you were at the school, finished up down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you go the same sort of hours at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, they were same hours, unless - unless it were half past four, I've forgot - to be exact. Believe it were half past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was the British school a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. Board school, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was that mixed or just boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, that were boys. Aye. Boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 The other one was a mixed one wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Ah that was all boys there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have any special feelings about the British school or again did you just take it in your stride?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Not really, no, I just - got to go and I - I - used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you feel about those teachers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well, same as I say I didn't - didn't feel not wrong about 'em, I didn't feel not bit so good about 'em. Just - they were teacher and that
 were it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 At this school did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No, they didn't - emphasise not - like that, they just - gave you lessons and - that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What about things like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh they used to 
learn you manners. Specially the - at top - top school. There were no better man - better man breathing as learn you manners. Pavement manners and everything he used to learn you. Step if you - any - anybody old - needed a - walking ground, you know, and 
don't stand in twos and - used to do learn you all that do you see and now - they're not learnt it, you can tell that. Tell that now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What else did they teach you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well practically everything - as regards - manners, you know what I mean
. Behaving yourself. They were more strict on that than what they were on education. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What about things like tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, used to - like you to be tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did punctuality come into it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, like to be punctual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What about ways of speaking, did either of the schools go in for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Speaking? No. There wasn't much of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 At Calverton Road if you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 If we done anything? Well they used to send you up to the school - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 to}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  the head}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 master,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
that was about all. He used to get a - he used to have a back pocket with a flat board in. You'd get four or five of them. Flat hand. That were - that were your punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did this flat stick have a special name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, it had a little handle - handle to it and it were flat, he used to just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was it a bit like a butter pat or something?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, not - not quite so broad. About that - about that broad you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 It wasn't a cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, flat board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did girls get the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
I don't know 'cos - I believe - I don't think we were in mixed - mixed classes. Think the girls were in - can't remember being in mixed classes, only - only -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Wasn't Calverton Road mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 No, they were mixed - but there was girls' classes and boys' classes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Aye. Aye, they were - when they were in infants if I remember right they were mixed. But after you got like a infant - bit older than infants - there were girls classes and - and boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What offences would you have got the flat board for, what sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - if any - bit hard to say because you didn't know sometimes what you got it for. If you weren't - if they thought you wasn't taking enough notice and that, not interesting yourself enough, anything like that pull you up over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well they'd no - they never had no reports then. Never sent no reports or like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, they used to ask us what we'd done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Can't remember - ever visiting. No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Pretty near. Not quite such big families though. Some of 'em were rough in a way of speaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In what sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - not looked after so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Any what groups? No. No, no groups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I don't think there were any that were left out, but you were - you were out in a way of speaking if they thought you - behind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In what sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I mean same as I - same as me - missing - school - all them years - in a way of speaking I was behind. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was it really years you missed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I missed practically - practically the whole of the year. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Then you were behind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well you were like left. You see if you - if you didn't gather it you - you'd lost it. My meaning is - it didn't - didn't put you back and - and let that year go, you kept go
ing forward. Aye, you kept going forward with class - 'til you got certain age and then you - then you - they used to keep you back. But you were still behind. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 
Because you - you couldn't - you couldn't jump a class and - and still be - on a level with them other lads - lads. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
You see, that's where I - that's how - oh yes. No, you passed - passed out of infants and then you was - then you went up in class, what they call classes. That's why I were a bit late going down to the British. That's what made me as I
 was only down there - about two year instead of perhaps three. Because I didn't get to me -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you got to the British had you sort of caught up by then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you - when it finished, you - it don't matter whether you caught up or not - you - you'd just got to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Thirteen and a half.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would you have stayed on longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you receive any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No. In fact I didn't know of none then. I sent my lads down to - night school when they were - after they finished school. They used to go down to - that where it is on - Shakespeare Street, for their - for their trades.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you have any regrets that it was like it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh aye. Oh aye, I regret - I reckon I should have been a - a little bit better if I hadn't have missed my schooling. I mean, I - I was - witty enough and all t
hat but you see - but you see you - you got that - that slip out and you was - you was - you was still without it. Because I - I do know - when I went to work at Sherwood Laundry - van lading, you see you had to make the sheets out and - and - and spell. 
And when I first start I could - I couldn't hardly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 spell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  some o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 f}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  it, I used to have to - copy 'em all off. Never wrong in me money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You picked it up quite quickly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Aye, I picked it up but I mean - it gave me that - you see, if I'd had a - a 
better chance - I should have been something better - bit better somewhere, shouldn't have been worse anyway. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you think you benefitted from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye. Oh aye. Oh aye, benefitted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Didn't have a part time job but in holidays I used to go to work - if I could get any. Weeding and - farm - bit of farm work and - gardening. Anywhere where you could go to - nurse - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 nursing}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  or gardening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How old would you have been when you started doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh about ten. Aye. First job I went to - oh - or pretty near the first, when Miss Thomas first come up Derrymount. That's Daybrook up there before him. It'd be about - 19
04. I should be ten. Fresh'un - fresh'un come up. I says to mother I says, fresh 'uns gone up mother, shall I go and ask him if I got a job for him? She said, please yourself, if you want - you can go. So I said, I will then. I went up and - got a job ple
ase. Aye. And when we'd finished, he come round - here you are lad. He was giving all lads a penny. He said, I think you've done a bit more work than others, I - and he give me tuppence.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How long had you worked for the tuppence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I'd been there -
 quite a - eight or - seven or eight - hours or something like that you know. So I went home, I said, here you are mother. This lot Mr Thomas' has given me, you can have it. Give it mother. Says she, is that all he give you? I says, yes. She says, did you
 
go and ask him for the job? I says, yes. So she write a note, you may be sure I couldn't read it. Same as I say, I - I were - I were that - that - that behind I couldn't read it, I took it next time. Oh he said, I forgot to set you on my lad. He gave me a
n
other eightpence. That was all you could claim then. Tenpence a day. So I went home and - straight away my mother sent me down to the butchers for - for two or three bits of meat with it. That's how we were fixed. Waiting for them two or three coppers to 
get a bit of - bit of meat, yes, aye, that's how we were fixed then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And if your mother hadn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 intervened}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  you would only have got the tuppence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 If what? I'd have got tuppence. You see - his idea was - they'll go and spend it, the mothers and dads not know}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 ing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 nowt }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
about it. But I took mine home. You see, that's - that's a - well that's what I always think. Mind you he had some of lads - lads a penny - that'd only been romping about you know. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How often did you do this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
What, work? Oh I used to do it often. Aye, used to go to - ladies across - across the road - gardening, Mrs Robertson lived on that hill going up Derrymount, that big - big house with - wall round you know. She were - lived on her own, well she had got a 
- she'd got a servant living with her that was all, she'd got no - there was no man. And me brother Bill had been up - been - up to time going to work. He says, you can that - manage that job at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Robertson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 , he says, you - you can go across now any time, do
 a bit of - gardening. So of course I went. And I - been there quite a - quite a - few nights and - and that - I daresn't hardly tell you what - what happened. But anyway - I put it - I - I took short, and - I thought to myself well I - I shan't have time
 to get home to get to the - get the - we used to call 'em closets then, get to the closet. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 
And I were up - right up top end of garden and there were big thick privet hedge, and there were hole in it - I thought to myself, I'll get in here. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I got - I got in
 there - and - and while I sat there, Mrs Robertson and another lady were coming walking up path. See? So I - backed further back in hedge. Got further back so they wouldn't - thinking they wouldn't see me. They walked by, they didn't see me, and I though
t they hadn't seen me. And it went on - some - some while after, anyway - I got a lot of hours in that - what do you call it - Champion Street. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
