s
ays, you can sort some bulbs over. So - when - when I looked up there he were at window - watching me. Chewing his meat. Watching me. So I took no notice for the first time. So he come - he come again, I - he was looking - looking. He was dubious of me do
 
you see. So, I went - like that to him. I don't know that they called it. So - he says - he comes rushing out, and he was still chewing his meat, when he come out. He says, what do you mean with that? I said, you know what I mean. He says, Mrs Robertson s
a
id you weren't as good as lad as your brother Bill. See? Well I rumbled then why - why he were watching do you see, she - so I said, I'm as good a man - good a man as you, I said, let's do it best of two. So he says, clear off home. I said, aye, when you'
v
e give me my coppers. He says - well that's how me character went. Just shows - just shows you how - how you can lose your character don't it, you see. She'd told him that I was sitting in - in the hedge, instead of being at work. Over that. And that's wh
a
t made him - shifting me from one job to another - so he could - so that he could see me. See that I was still working. And that - that - that's how it come about. I - I weighed it up after. How - and there you are, that' shows you how you - can lose your
 character.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What other sort of jobs like that did you do when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh thinning turnips. Tagging turnips. Weeding and - these other - market gardeners and flowers and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What were you paid then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Mind you, that was a - used to pay - if you were lucky you got a shilling. A day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But it might have been tenpence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Some of 'em gave you tenpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well you know, at that time tenpence was worth - a lot same as it was what - in fact what two to three tenpence would - would fetch today.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you always give this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh ayes, used to always take to mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And it was spent on food and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Food and - what bit of - perhaps buy a bit of something to wear or something of that if she - could afford it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh all right. I never had no trouble with 'em, that's - the only trouble I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did your other employers treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - I used to get on with them all right, such as Stanfield at - Stocking farm there. I went for him quite a while. When we got down at bottom of - field - them houses that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 \endash }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Lepool}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9707487  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
houses - back - come into his fie
ld like. So - Mr Williams who lived in that - that row where that - garage is now at Lepool - come to Mr Stanfield, so Stanfield was talking to him - he says - you've got some - I believe you've got a tidy strawberry bed George. He says, aye, he says, and
 
some of your chaps - knows I have. See? He says, they come through. He says, you know - if they'd ask me I'd give 'em one or two. So I says, give us one or two then. He says, give me your hat me lad, he said, let's put you - put you some in your hat. Go a
nd sit down and eat 'em. Aye. Just the difference you see. Aye. And he were only - do you see, when he was - he says, well give us one or two then. You could have one or two. Got strawberries there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you feel about your employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh I used to respect 'em. Some of 'em anyway, most on 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh I didn't bother about the work, I just - worked if you follow me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I used to like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did having these jobs alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
I got that - I got the opportunity - going that - that outing with 'em when I went to Trentbridge you see. Or work. I went to work. So I must have liked it. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you left school what was your first full time job, was it selling the vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Selling vegetables. Selling - selling vegetables. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you go about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I used to go and buy half a crown's worth of onions and radishes from Mr Andrews. And he used to lend you a square - square b
asket. Used to get it under your arm and go round from door to door. Selling 'em. Four bunches a penny. You could have - two of radishes, two of - and two of onions. Or three and a one, which you liked, for a penny then. And I - and I could earn more - th
an what I could going on vans.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So how much did you earn then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
And that - I used to go about two o'clock, to buy me - to buy me - half a crown's worth. And then - I should perhaps be finished at round about - sometimes six to seven - at night. Be
fore I sold out - used to stop out 'til I'd sold up. Sold up you know. Well then my brother, he started baking. In Morris Street. And I used to go selling buns and barn loaves for him. Fridays and - Saturday. And I could earn a - quite a few coppers off o
f him then. Well I got as I could earn more money than going finding a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So how much would you be earning at that stage roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I used to reckon I could earn - about - two shilling out of that half a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 
crown\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  worth of - aye, aye, used to recko
n I could earn - is what - I had about - two - two shilling. Well you got a basket as you could - you could hardly carry you know for half a crown then. With these onions and radishes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So this was fairly seasonal, what did you do when the winter came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh used to sell red cabbage and - bits like that, but I mean it was - when they were out you - you were out you see, you'd to - well then me sister she started this shop down at - bottom of High Street, it were greengrocers. I used to go selling ora
nges for her. Oranges and dates. Specially if there's a cricket match, when they used to play cricket on that - before it were richer, the barbers - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  barbers like had a cricket club as played on that - where the recreation is now at Derrymount. An
d I used to go take 'em on there - to sell. Oranges and dates. And bits and - bobs like that. Make coppers that road. That was Saturday afternoon. Not cross bun day we used to have a - proper battle - with different bakers. Well - well me and me brother u
s
ed to - me brother was a - getting - Harold - he were getting one thing and another and selling. So - Mr Baldwin's shop - shop the - bun shop up - bakers shop up Front Street and I - Jack were down at - Murray Street. So R used to go and get me - buns and
 me and we used to go and have a - this Baldwin was selling - his - hot cross buns on his own. So - when he - when he'd got down - same as this yard, I used to sand our Harold on at front, so as he - so as he went round where he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You raced him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Yes, where he'd been - where he'd been to - to lose his time do you see. Two - two yards in front. I said, you go and - and - and we passed - we'll be in front of him that road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What after that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I - I think I - after that time I went down to Sherwood. Sherwood Laundry. Van lading. After then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you get the van lad job, did you get it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, I went and asked for it myself. I - I believe -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What hours did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I believe it were an advert in - on the front - on - I went round looking round and I think there were advert on front - }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Sharwood}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  Laundry, went in and got it. That's how I got that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Where was the Sherwood Laundry? You don't mean Daybrook do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, Sherwood. Nottingham Laundry 
at Sherwood it was to be exact. It was - where that - supermarket is - not Fine Fare, the other one, the other side, down at - nearly at bottom of the hill. Just above - above where buses goes in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What hours did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We used to get th
ere at eight o'clock in the morning but we never knowed when we were coming home. I've been - I've been all night there one night. Aye. We was in Beeston Square when stop - Sherwood. Nottingham Laundry Sherwood. We'd been round - Beeston and Attenborough 
t
hat day, delivering. And it had been foggy practically all day. We'd had to lead us horses all - or near enough all the way round. We got - there weren't no cars then you know, it were all horses. And I was - coming home - I were leaning on the coaches si
d
e and van man were learning on the inside as that clock in - in - Beeston Square struck twelve. And we'd got to go to Sherwood then. And it still hang on, and I don't know just what time it were when we landed in Sherwood but somewhere around about half p
a
st one time. So - this man that I were van - van - lading with, he says, you're not going home tonight are you Walt? I says, I shall have to go home, I says, I've no option. Oh, he says, I shouldn't go, I should bed down here. He said, I'll bring you some
 
- what food you want tomorrow. I'll bring you something for breakfast and something to take out - take out with you, we take us - if we're out on a day journey we take us food with us, if we're not we used to have it in saddle room. So - bit of persuasion
, he said, I said - not much. So, I took it on, he bedded me down in - in the - in that front office, with some - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 bedcloth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6236194\charrsid9707487 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 and one thing and another from - out of the laundry you know, and I - I got down I. When I got home the next night mother had been up all night. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But she must have known how foggy it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Aye, she knew it was foggy but - she - she never went to bed. She said, I never went to bed. Waiting. She said, and then when - when you never come in she said - I give it in, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6236194\charrsid9707487 nowt}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  happened, I said. See? Aye. But I said you're not doing - I'm not stopping there all night again }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Johnny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 , I said, it don't matter how late it is.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you ever work Sundays at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no, never had to do Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Saturdays or was that a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh no, full shift Saturday. Aye, sometimes later than ever. At average - as average was - on a Monday - we used to get done early. Because we were collecting. We could start out in the morning and go straight about us business and get done. T
uesday were collecting. Wednesday was collecting a little bit then delivering a little bit. But when it were delivering, if it weren't ready you had to wait round for it. So you got - got out - for out later. On a Thursday - your load weren't ready 'til s
e
ven o'clock at night, and we'd been there - all day, and that-s when I went and got job at Sherwood. Aye, got job at - at Gedling while I were waiting for me journey - being ready, for seven. About round about seven. But then - Saturday - we used to be - 
sometimes to about half past six. On average it'd be about half past six Saturday nights before we got finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was Friday a very late night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Friday was pretty late. Round about six, something like that. That's if we could get round - it if were
n't foggy or - clear, when it were clear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 There were no holidays with pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you get Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What - what bit of holiday we had there - we had to pull us weight so we got what - what was to 
be done in a week we - we got other weeks. You see, we like got it to a way of speaking there. But we had to pull us weight in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You had to get it done just the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. We'd got to pull us work in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What were you paid at the laundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When I left I was earning twelve shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did you start at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I've forgot the exact figure but it wouldn't be above seven.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you feel it was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, it wasn't. I went in - just before, I went after that 
job - and the manageress said, you're getting more than any lad on job. I said, well God help them that are getting less, I said. Aye. So she - I don't know whether she was pulling the leg or - telling me a lie or what, but that's what she told me. She sa
id, you're getting more - more than any of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 At this stage were you giving it all to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Aye. I used to give it all and then - I used to tell her as I could make my bit of spending money. Aye, because - and how I used to make it - so
me'd give you - if it were - two and ten or - some'd perhaps give you an odd tuppence or penny see, say you have that my lad. Well then it - if they didn't - I ain't got no - you see, you have it when you can, it's all right. Sometimes with a - stock - st
o
ck keeper, and he - he were like just higher - at getting it out. It was like - in a way of speaking - manager over that department you see. So - one of my mates, he - he went and got on at Gedling, a week or two - week - a week or so before - before I di
d
. Well when he - he was short handed on - on Monday, that Monday - that morning when we went work, after Monday it were, he said, you know we're short handed. He said, Weekly's left. So he said - he says, you go and do such a job, before you go out. You g
o and do such a job. You go and do such a job. That were about four on us, go and do such - pulling his work in. So I said, how much of Weekly's money am I going to have when I've done that then? Oh, he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 said}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 , as long as you get ready for going out it'll be 
all right. You - you're not - you'll be ready for - be able to go out - out as usual. I said, if I like - if I'm going to do so much of Weaver's work I want so much of Weaver's money. So he said, well, he said, I'm telling you, that's it. He said, well, h
e
 said, if you don't go and do it, he said, you'll have to go and see Miss Thorpe. That were manageress. So I said, well I might as well go now then because I shan't do it. See.. I were like on strike on me own. So - it went on. And I were just taking the 
h
orses up, he said, have you been and done that Walt? I said, you know very well I weren't going to do it, I told you I weren't going to do it. He says, well you'd better go and see what she says. I says, ah, I will. So I goes in - says, what's the matter 
M
artin? I says, not the matter with me, I says, why? She said, what have you come for? I said, I don't know, I said. So she says, why - what's the trouble? I said, I want so much of Weaver's money, I said, if I'm going to do them jobs. So - when I started 
talking like that she said, go and get about your errands, let's hear no more about it. She just said, let's say no more about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you get any extra?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. I didn't do the work. No, I didn't do the work. But these others got not extra - as went and come it. They didn't get not extra.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So what happened the week after?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh I was gone. I went and got job same - same week, same - same - I left on Saturday. And I says to her, I says, shall you give me a character? She says, I bet you don't want one where you're going. She'd a bit of idea I was following Weaver like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you get on with the other people you worked with at that firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh all right. Aye. Specially man - me own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6236194\charrsid9707487 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6236194\charrsid9707487 van man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you feel about the work there, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - oh aye, I used to like it. I used to enjoy. If it were nice it were - it weren't too heavy job you know and out in country a bit and Beeston were like a country place then and Attenborough. Sometimes - odd time we used to go to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Long Eaton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 . Beechford. And - Stoke. I've been down that Stoke Lane - when there's water each -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 That's Stoke Bardold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Been down there when - water reached up to - horses - top of it's leg nearly - Aye. Down that lane with 'em. Aye. S
ame at Beeston. On that Queens Road. Where the - station, know where I mean, where the station is. All under water. Aye. That - I've seen Beeston station lying all under water when I were there. Aye. All down that Trent Lane, same - same here. Right up to
 Attenborough. Attenborough were flooded. All up there. That'd be about - about 1911. 1910 or '11, somewhere about then. Aye. As near as I can tell you mind you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You told me how you got your job at Gedling pit, what hours did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When
 we first started we used to go down the pit at six, but I - I think - the proper time was - if I remember right were half past six 'til - 'til two. Seven - or else seven 'til two, seven - seven 'til two I think the hours. But you used to be starting goin
g
 down pit for six. For starting mind you but there'd always be some - going down 'til seven do you see, nearly seven, but they stopped winding at seven. So I mean if they all wanted to get down last five minutes they couldn't have done it. No, see, so - b
oys had to start at - an hour sooner to wind them down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So it was sort of seven 'til two was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Now what would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 That's seven hours, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I believe it - aye, it'd be later. It'd be - it'd be half - help past six 'til half past two I'll bet then. At that time of day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you work Saturdays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well not many Saturdays then. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 
Only Saturday - odd Saturday unless they were - only during war, you could work Saturdays and Sundays any time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 During - '14 war. Before wer
en't - weren't - weren't much Saturday work. Up to '14 war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have any holidays with pay then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What were you paid in the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 First holidays with pay as I - as I got - I was at Calverton pit, but working under Bestwood. They
 used to send men down at - Calverton with one shaft, and call 'em up at Bestwood then. That were - that - aye, connected underneath. That were - we went there in - 1939 and come away in - '48. And it was during that time when - holidays with pay come in.
 So I think it - to be about right it'd be about right it'd be about 1944.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What about pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 One week. One week - holiday pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did you get when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 At - pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 It was a lot more than the laundry wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye
, it were better than - better money than the laundry, but it was so much a day you see. You got paid daily. I just forget how much'd it'd be then. I got started at, I should be here what - sixteen when I went. Be about sixteen. Perhaps - perhaps seventee
n. Might have been seventeen when I went. I know it were - round about - between - four to six shilling. Somewhere about that a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was that the sort of rate that you stayed at for a long time or did you go up with experience?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh well you - oh w
hen you - when you got - old - bit older, I weren't there long afore I was on - started working on coalface you see. Then you got a little - bit more money you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What would it have been when you started on the coalface?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - full price at that time - that were just - just - previous to '14 war. Ten and fourpence for full - for top pay. Unless the b}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 oss\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  - doing well and perhaps he'd give you another tanner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So this was ten and fourpence a day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Ten and fourpence a day, that was all you could }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 claim}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
. Unless you got extra from - man as you're working under. Well apprentice price'd be about - seven or eight shilling. Perhaps - perhaps seven, seven and a tanner, at that time of day. Then - then as you got older do you see - you got the 
same pay as them, as he - as he got - as he learnt his job, what they call - you were so - so - supposed to be so long an apprentice but if butty thought you was a - qualified at doing - as many tubs as - as this - this qualified you started getting your 
- your money same as him you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You were quite quickly on the full pay were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I weren't all that long. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you an apprentice for long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. They didn't apprentice you long really - you're supposed to - it - it were - supposed
 to be two year - as apprentice, but - if you got as you could - took your - coal on same as ordinary man he used to - pay you - what they call full money you see. Get your full money then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So you were there before the two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, got me full money before two year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you feel it was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well it weren't a fair wage. But that's what - what caused - caused a - what were - first strike were in '21. '21, that first strike, that were over money you know. Over wages - poor wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 At this stage were you giving the money to your mother in the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Aye, used to - give it to her, she used to give us so much - spending money back. 'Til we got on what we called board, and I used to give her good board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When would you have gone on to board?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I bet it'd be about twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you were down the pit how did you get on with the other people you were working with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh got on all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you feel the employer treated you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Nev
er had any - any - trouble with any of 'em that I know to. Well you - we used to go - have a bit same as anywhere else like, bits of tiff with one another. Didn't always see eye to eye with - everybody.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who was your employer in those days, did you ever see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Very rare. Dennis Bailey were - Dennis Bailey owned Gedling - at that time. Then - he got to be Sir Dennis Bailey later. He - he were the owner. Or the main owner anyway. But he were the main owner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We never see'd him. Well I never - I never seen him. I don't think anyone did see him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh - you used to have to be satisfied and you used to get on with your work and - get it done and that were it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh I liked it all right, I wasn't bothered about work. Anyway work never bothered me. I never let work bother me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there a very close feeling among the people you worked with - what did you call a group of people who worked together down a pit?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there like a gang or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well you - you'd get a number - you'd all get a number and you were - get your number, that were - all. When you used to get there in the morning you - about - number tw
enty-four, and you'd put your mark on, and there weren't - didn't call you - gangs or anything -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there a word for the people who worked for one butty man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We worked for - when you were - when you were what you called day working, that's - you working for that buttyman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there any name for the group of you who worked together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Daymen. Daymen. Aye, they were daymen. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 He was butty and you were day man. }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. You got day's pay. That -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there a very sort of close feeling between the people who worked together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
In - in some cases. Well you know, being in some cases as you got as you'd like 'em but - you'd always that bit of - back of your mind that - you were getting - robbed or twisted. You see, but you - you - you got a 
bit more liking for some of 'em than others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did having this sort of job alter your attitude to school? Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, don't know as I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You changed in the end to training other people didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Aye, last - last few years. Oh I went to - several - I - I - I went on to - training one lad, coal - coalface work, for - for a few years before I started train - what they call training instructor. What used term as a - used to have to - learn h
im all as - all there was to be learnt about coalface work. Coalface only, you see. And - and bring him out. That's the one, and you'd got him under you perhaps for - for - four or five - say four to six months sometimes. Then he - he - he went - went on 
t
o the coal face on his - he were ready. Well then - I got me arm broke on that job. In - in '54. And I should be sixty then. Sixty years of age. So I thought myself, it's time I - packed coalface up now. And that's when I went and asked for this - trainin
g
 job. In fact I went and - demanded it in a way of speaking. I knew the man as were over it, and - he'd been deputy and he knew me - knew - we knew one another well like. So I went to him, I says, now George, says, I want a job under you. He says, well, h
e
 says - if it's left to me Walt, he says, you're just the man I want. See? He says, if gaffer'll let you come, he says - job's there. I said, right. So it went on. I went and found. - gaffer. Oh he said, I think you'll be all right, he said, but we've got
 to go through credentials, you know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 the routine, he said. Come up next Friday. I - I had took off - off to go to work then, I was still on - compensation do you see. So - come up next Friday, he said, you aren't working? I said, no, I says, I'm not 
going to work 'til I get this job. So he says, all right. So - when it gets up following Friday - I couldn't find him. It went on. And then another man come walking by, he said, are you after a job Walt? Aye, I said, I am Tom. He was. - his name were Tom.
 
He said, I'll find you a job, he said, and a good 'un. See? I said, all right Tom, I said, but I'm after one, I'm after one certain job, I said, but if I don't manage what I'm after, I said, I'll come and see what you've got. Thank you. See? So - this wen
t
 on - quite a few more minutes, I kept looking round to see if I could find this - manager I were looking for. I forget his name now, Mr - I'll think of it in a minute - but anyway his next man was in, Mr Brown. I said, Mr Brown, I said, where's Mr - aye,
 
Mr Ogden. I said, where's Mr Ogden? Oh, he said, he's just been called off, he said, he's got - he's had to go to a - some - executive meeting or something, I just forget how to pronounce it. He said, I know what you're after. He said, you're all, right, 
h
e said, you're through. Go and tell - you've got best job you've ever had in your life. See? So I went to Gamble, I says, all right then. When are you going to start then? Well, I'll start Monday guv'nor. So all right, we - we started. Well you'd got to t
a
ke these five lads - round with you. And learn 'em what they call the - high side of pit. You see, like the pit work. Not actually doing it, they didn't have to actually do it. They'd got to - learn 'em about pit sense, you see, and take 'em round with yo
u
 and - learn 'em - showing how they pack and how they get coal and how they - put the - support the roof and everything. You see, and you - you have 'em three month. And during that three month they went to - school alternate weeks and you - and it made '
em like six month altogether. Then they went to - to the different pits - to work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Which pit was this you were teaching them in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Be at Bestwood. But they - some of these lads come from - Gedling, Calverton, Cinderhill, Upnall pit, they come from
 all over to this - to this centre do you see. And - I says to - I says to one - one of the lads at Friday when he - no, Thursday they used to give 'em the docket. And he - they used to give 'em a docket then, it were - just about as big as that, full of 
-
 different items. Of course there were all dockets made out for different - for all - so they could put all different jobs in like you see, that's why they were bigger than what they were - ordinary got you see. I said, look at that now. I said, there's a
 
docket, I said, when I first started at pit I said, they used to give us a little bit of paper and it says, wages four and eleven. You see. He says - it was a bit more than four and eleven like, but I just termed it at that. I said, and that was all we go
t. He said, were it? I said, aye, I said, do you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6236194\charrsid9707487 I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
said, I killed a pony with kindness. He said, you did? I said, aye. I said, I did. I said, I were on afternoon shift - I said, and when I got down pit I happened to put me - me fingers in me waistcoat
 pocket and I pulled this 'ere little slip out, I said, and pony shafter and - I just hear him on his tubs and I says, hey up, I says. Now }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 look}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  'ere old lad, I've got me new rate. And, I says, he rolled over and died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. I said - I told - I told him killed him with kindness. I said, look here, what you and me did, I said, they're paying you }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 naught,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 I said, there's me and you's earnt this. I said, and - it - one and - out of five - were a bit more witty than others, he said, how could he read? I said, I don't know, but anyway he read it. He said, how could that pony read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I thought you meant the pony had a heart attack at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No, it - it were a joke with 'em. I told 'em - I told 'em, I said, I killed him wi
th kindness. He said, how did you manage that then? And that's how I told you. Aye, I says, I showed him a docket, I said, you're - you've got a docket there as bi- as huge wall I says, and I got this little bit of paper to kill him. I said, and all it sa
id on wages so much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, belonged miners. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Miners\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. Only just paid me union and - going to odd meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You didn't enter into it very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh no. Very few - 'cos they used to have - mostly have 'em at Bulwell, that were one - handicap with us. Majority of the - Bestwood workers come from Bulwell at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you feel that the employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well they hadn't got same. No. When it were owned - private enterprise - gaffers always - thought you held a - grudge in a way of speaking. Aye. Oh aye, gaffers used to use you - for then. But after it got - nationalised - they did hav
e a bit more respect for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But when you were young you felt there was a huge difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, were - different - difference in - in a different class altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers? Did you feel different workers had different interests in the job?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Some of - did I feel different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you feel there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 The workers? Oh aye, were some - under - different interests than others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In what sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well, some'd - if there were any chance of dodging they would do and if there were any - and others - were conscientious they used to get on with the work in any case, get it done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Some people say in those days there were great divisions among trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - as regards coalface - there weren't no - what we call trained craftsmen. There were some better workmen than others. But since this - since they've got this machinery
 in now they've got to be like a craftsman. More - more so than - than what they had at that day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 They were pretty skilled in that day were'nt - they?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They were skilled as regards getting coal. And - and - and - supporting the roof, and all tha
t, but that were - there were no machinery - to be skilled about you see, it were just the job - as they were skilled on. It were like a man working on the land. If he knows his job he - he can do better than what that lad - that man as comes as don't kno
w his job you see. You were skilled as regards knowing your job. But my meaning is there were no - machinery to be skilled over. There were no machine work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there a great deal of difference between the people who worked at the coalface and the peop
le who worked else where, above ground or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well, the coalface man got most money, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did he get more respect or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no, no more respect than just the ordinary workman same as them. Just - just ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh no, no, the - attitude, you got - went on your normal way, just as usual. No, they used to get - bit more money than - than the - men round him. Same - same as up and - j
ibber, you got more money than - driver got most money. Colliers, they get according like to - how much they were filling off, at one time they used to get paid the tonnage. Well then when they got these belts - the belts in, as took it - right up to pit 
top at Bestwood, they done away with that tonnage because - they couldn't weight it. See, so they had to make it like - what they called averaged. Means when you got one out there's so much to divide }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6236194\charrsid9707487 among}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  you. You see. So it depends how many men there is w
orking - as regards how much money you get. This is - this is colliers you see. That's how it was. They made us as take this Webb rate on because - I can remember saying to Mr Reece who was the manager then. He - he dropped it. He says, we don't want Webb
 
rate. So - I says, now look here Mr Reece, I says, you say you don't want Webb rate and still you are having to have it. I says, that ain't much recommended to us. I said, if you don't want it - I said, I'm sure it ain't much cop to us. You see. He says, 
oh it will be, he says, you'll be all right, he says, in fact I think you'll be better off. And we was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Why did they used the word Webb?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Ah - this is a Webb. When you - when you fetch that - that four foot off as is cut as - cut you see. And you'
ve cut that so much and you've got to tear it all off, that's your Webber. Right from there, that's - hundred and thirty yards each - each side as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 It's always a hundred and thirty yards is it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, they don't - they don't always - we - we had 
one - we had one at Calveton as were two hundred but they done away with it, it got - it was too far. Belts used to break too much. When they - when they got too long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So it was normally a hundred and thirty yards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, used to run it round - ro
und about a hundred thirty - a hundred and twenty to a hundred and thirty yards. After then - after that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you tell me about your life at home after you left school, you stayed living at home didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When - I were - it - it - we haven't got to where baths started have we? We haven't got to where baths started at pit have we? Well -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was that after 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Baths - weren't in at - at Bestwood 'til 1933. We - we'd got no baths at - 1918. No. It were 1933 when first bath were in 
there. And - up to - up to like that time you could - you couldn't get a - respectable drink of water at pit. No. When I worked at Gedling I never - did see where you could get a drink of water. And I left in 1926. Well - 1927 to be exact. Early 1927.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you take any active part in getting conditions any better down the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No, they used to - they picked on different deputations odd times as represent daymen. What they call representing daymen. Used to meet - if there were any - troubles as regards wages and - that, I've been on one or two deputations for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But you weren't very tied up in the trade union were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. Oh no. No, never tied up with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Before 1918 did you take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. I never took 
no interest in politics. Practically all me life. No, only just voting - with me vote, using me vote like. And that's been Labour - this last - good many years now. Because I always reckon Labour done us more good than Tories. You see, that's why - that's
 why they got it. Well there's no doubt about it they done us a good turn Labour did in that - with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 nationalisation}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
, they nationalised mines. There's no doubt about that. Because up - before then I mean - miners were in not such a good - life as - as they had after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anyone to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Any pressure? Oh no. No. No, they've been - and canvassed me - to vote but - not used any pressure. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you an actual member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I were - member of Liberal club but it weren't the - it weren't the party. No. Never been a - never been a member of no party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you first started work you were still living at home weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did starting to work full time change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 It didn't make you feel more independent or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. No. No. I - didn't make me feel no independence, it made me feel - feel a bit more independent - as I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 owed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  'em a bob or two. Aye, that were more my attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did it alter you relationship - with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No, they never altered, we were - about the same - rough and ready - always that attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 When you started work did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you please yourself any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Not - not - not at first off. Not for a long long while. But - it - it started afte
r that - I told you about that Bible class - breaking up. And I should be - round about twenty-three I'll bet, twenty three years of age - of age - twenty-three, well - up to the time of - I'll bet it would be about - about twenty-two or twenty-three and 
Mr Arnold died. Then - and then Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Broml}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6236194\charrsid9707487 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 took class over. And it went just like hat, and - and I don't know whether it was two month or a little over two month and - I'm not coming again. And I'm not coming again, that's how it was. There - there were cla
ss of twenty-four in it. All young men, and I were about youngest - youngest. And all the time Mr Arnold had got it it were just same as going home. And you were just as welcome as you were - war going on. And he come you know, he were a bit more bombast 
you see and trying to bombast. It - it killed it. Well then after we started going a bit - as he liked you know. There was nowhere - nowwhere to go. So we used to go out bike riding or anything of that do you see, Sunday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you still go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Not after - left choir. No. Well - odd time, it were - odd time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How long did you stay in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh quite a few years. Up to me voice breaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you tell me how you spent your spare time in that time when you started work? Were you doing many different things from when you }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6236194\charrsid9707487 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
We used to - we used to be the footballing and - go out a bit - bit more like. Didn't have a lot of money you know. And - and we used to go out biking if it were - bike a bit if it was a decent night, have a ride round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How far would you get on your bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well round Southwell and - round that way. Mostly we used to cycle Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And you were still playing football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 By that time did you ever go to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh ah, we used to go down to - Empire or - Hippodrome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you go much to the Empire and the Hippodrome?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, just occasionally. After I got - when we got to Sherwood we used to go in every Tuesday. And do you know how much it 
cost us? There was about five of us lads there then, all - round about - anything from - fourteen to sixteen years of age you know. So we used to say, how much have you got this morning? And it - Tuesday we could always guarantee at getting done - do you 
s
ee, about time as we - wanted to go down to the - Hippodrome, it was about - I think about six o'clock time we would go in. Oh I've got tuppence, I've got - penny. And that lad as worked in yard and stable lad he couldn't - go out and - earn - make nothin
g
 you know. So - them as were on vans - had to try their best to make enough - for the lot, you see. For all on 'em. So that it - so that it worked out we'd got sixpence a piece. You see, And that's what it cost us. And we used to have a penny ride on the 
tram. And a - that were - only went to Sherwood then, you couldn't ride to Arnold if you wanted to. But we rode it Sherwood very likely going down. Tuppence up into gallery. And a penny back. And tuppence to spend.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did you get with your tuppence to spend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - perhaps a bun or - a - sometimes penn'orth of chips, you know, anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So you'd have a real good night out for sixpence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Yes. We used to think we'd had a - a bust up. Had a good night out, but it was tuppence up in gallery then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember going to the cinema for the first time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well I don't remember first time. I used to - used to go to that one when they come in their - wooden hut. But I think I'd been to - either one or - or so before then. Ca
n't remember first time of course. But we used to go to that one in - back of police station. That were wooden hut we called it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 Dugout}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 . We used to call it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2101908\charrsid9707487 dugo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 ut. No, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 dugout}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  they used to call it. Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you go there often and what did that cost you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well I - I told you - Mr Anthony, he - he were only like taking tickets do you see, they'd got to go and get their tickets, and he were on side door - and you get your ticket at the - front, like a bit of - bit of a shed like. Blobholes we use
d to call 'em, get your ticket out, it were - aye, like a - you know, where the railwaymen used to give tickets through them little - pigeon holes you see. So - instead of going to him he started taking odd - pennies - off of lads and letting go. Some as 
he knew like. And then one or two got to know it and they followed on. 'Til it got as there was - too many using it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 About half of you got in without did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Aye. Penny, if you'd a penny. And it were only - I don't know whether it was only 
about tuppence to go in - proper - proper price like then. But mind you that's - it'd be - before - it'd be before '14 war I believe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you go anywhere else in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, we didn't used to go out a deal at night. Not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You went to the Hippodrome on Tuesday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Tuesday, we used to go down - aye, but we were working then at - Sherwood. Working all day Saturday - when we were at Sherwood. It was father we - when we got to the pits as went out a bit of - biking Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you make any new friends, boys or girls, at this time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 We used to make - different lad friends but - never made no girl friends, I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you ever bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I did take one lad home - a bit - one time - one time. The only girl I took home - were my wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you meet her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
I were - I were - well I were twenty-eight and she was thirty-two when we got married. So we weren't children. And I think we'd been together about three year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How did you actually meet her, was she a local girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No, she was Longton. And I went down to Goose Fair - on me own, that Saturday night. And I thought myself, I'll have a walk round Nottingham. And it - weren't interested in - in - fair. And the funny thing about it - I
 called in one of - public houses for a half pint of beer, and my wife were in there. And - she never drunk. The reason she was in - she'd been with her friend - her friend to - visit a - her aunt, her mother - her mother's sister, and - mother's sister h
a
d come - come in with 'em, and she says, come on in with me, I'm going to have a drink. And they - neither of these two drunk. They both had a lemonade. And I got talking to 'em - and - I should be about twenty-four. So - I said, are you going down to the
 
fair? So - me and her went to the fair. And we stopped there, I took her down home, down - then walked home, had to walk home - then. Walked home. So - I says, I asked her if we could meet again like, see her again. So we made arrangements and we went - w
e
nt on together then really. And that's how we - how we met and how we kept on. She used to come home with me after - after we - I'd been going with her a while, Sundays, she used to come home with me after - after we - I'd been going with her a while, Sun
days, she used to come Sunday. Sunday afternoon for tea you know. Then I used to go down their house sometime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents expect to meet your friends, did they expect you to bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well, no, they didn't make much - provisi
on for that. You know what I mean, with 'em having a big family the - they'd plenty on, they'd got plenty without in a way of speaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your parents expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well they pretty near always knew where - where - or - or thereabouts there - where you was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have to be home by a special time at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - in us younger days we did but not when we got a bit older like. We - after we got a bit of liberty. And they thought you could look after yourself a bit with - you could go in any time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you have any special friends at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No special girl friends or boy friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 She was a - a - our Nellie was only girl friend I ever - ever had, I had - I had one or two - different -
 to talk to you know and that but not - not to go with. No. You know - that's what I reckon they do wrong with these young people. They put too much - they put too much into 'em. Now - my mother and father, well - my father never said nothing to me. He us
ed to threaten you - this different road and tell you - you should know right from wrong, you see, that's how he give it you. If you play with fire you expect getting burnt, see - that's how we used to pass our time down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But the accepted way of the girls meeting boys was walking from Daybrook to Sherwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Yes, we walked from - from Daybrook - bridge - bridge were there then you know. Where bridge was. Aye. That were Daybrook bridge. Then used to walk backward and forwards - up and down - as far as Sherwood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And seeing how many people you met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Aye, that were proper - proper walk - at that time of day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was it a nice sort of a country walk then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, it were more - bit more country than it is now you know. There were t
hat - what they called Jacob's Ladder down there then and - and that - all - all open space right away - there was only - there was only one house and that was where Potter's - lived in a - in a cottage. There were - Coltswood's cottage. Then next was Ced
a
r's. Aye. And then - then from Cedar's there was farm - just - straight opposite Spout Lane, or Woodthorpe Drive as is now. It was Spout Lane then. Aye. And then there were this - Captain Thomas' where that - school is now for them - children. And that we
re all there were on that side. So - 'til you got over the hill. And - and there were very - very little on the other side - of the hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Where in Sherwood did the tram }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 start}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Trams used to come as far as - Sher - Winchester - Winchester Street. 
Aye, Winchester Street, that was terminus. Aye, just a bit up this side of bus station. That was - tram terminus. Tram terminus then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some pe
ople belonging to one and some to another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, there used to be but - I never mixed up with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you sort of mentally think of people in different sort of social classes or groups? Or did you think everybody was the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I used to think everybody were about same or - bit better off than one another, that was only - thing as I - I knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You sort of put people into whether they had more money than others did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye. They're better off than me or - that attitude like, which they was. In most cases.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of groups were there in those days, who were the sort of better off people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well you know, there were - better off people them as - got best jobs as far as I could - business men and - and that. They w
ere always better off people weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What groups would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well only - only thing I could - say working - working group. Working class group.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of people belonged to the same group as you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - that's all on 'em what were in same - occupation as yourself and - and on a level with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of people belonged to the other groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well, same as I say, business people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did this working class group you were mentioned have sub-divisions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, don't remember any. Sub-divisions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you lump everybody in the working class together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no, there'd be - there'd be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Can you tell me the groups in it in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They didn't for a group, it just a matter - well I don't know as they did. Don't know as they formed any group.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh no. No, we never - tutored anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you ever told to touch your cap to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Used to have to - touch your cap to the vicar at that time when we were lads but not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - there was different people but there weren't many as - as we touched it to, only vicar at that time,
 that - mind you that's - when we were in - the - church school, you see. But did - there was some of 'em that used to expect you to touch your had to 'em, what you call cap in hand like, there's a lot of cap in hand business if - if you went in - if you 
went anywhere to ask for a job it'd got to be cap in hand. Oh aye. Oh aye, went after a job in a office or anything of that. Got to have cap in hand then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In any other sort of situation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Practically all on 'em. For the lads. They'd expect it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you ever taught to show respect in any other way to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 taught}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  to respect people. Either old - old or the - infirm or any - anything, you was taught to respect people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were you told to show respect in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
That's what I - I said about - Miss Ellis. The old schoolmaster. He - I think he used to learn 'em more in that respect than what they do today. Aye. Because you used to learn it at - if there were any - pavements weren't so wide in that day as they are t
o
day - well, it'd only be about the width of this - of this table like. And if there were out like two or three standing anywhere - they'd got to step off causey. But he - he used to drill you that. Don't let an old - person get off the causey for you, you
 see. That - the schoolmaster. But I don't think they drill it - drill it today. Because I'd expect you - if I'm going down on this - narrow bit of causey down here - down to have a drink at club and there's a couple comes it, it's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6236194\charrsid9707487 means you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 got to get off.
 Yes. Now. Regular. They'll not part. And there's only just - proper good room for two. On that pavement just below - High Street Avenue there. And they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 The two stick together do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well they - they do, I've seen it, times out of many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was there anyone you called sir in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. Not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Used to call 'em master.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who did you call that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well you had to call the man - call the gaffers - Mr so and so and - to the gaffer, you know, Mr so and so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 My parents? Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In the district who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Some of these - well, what they call toffs anyway. Used to raise their hat 
you know. When they - when you were out with your mother. Raise their hat you see. The - some on 'em -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you go out without a hot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, there were very little - not at that time. Anybody - very few as - as went - well, hardly any I don't thin
k, time that I were lad I don't think there were any - any lads went - went out without a hat at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would you play without a hat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well you'd play without a hat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 But you couldn't walk out without one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, they'd pretty near all got a hot on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Would you have thought it was dreadful if they didn't have hats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well you didn't feel dressed did you at that time of day. Didn't feel dressed unless you'd got a hat. Used to - used to wear them little -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who were considered the most important people around here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - there were - quite a few as we used to reckon important, there was - Mr Acton in his day and there were - Farr's, Robinson's. Then 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 Jock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  Wardle, he got up - up into that - him as had Bughut picture palace, he got up into that - category a bit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who was Joe Wardle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Why - he was a councilor. He got on council and he - he used to do a - he used to - according to how I could - see it in his younger days - he used to do a lot of dealing. And - Mr Robin
son - he - he'd deal and all buy property and - you know, he went in property and this and that. And this Wardle got - got stung. Aye. And his mother - I don't know for certain whether it's true but they always say it's true, so she said, pack it in Joe. 
Y
ou know you're not - not - you're not clever enough for him. He says, that's just where you're wrong mother. He said, I've learnt my lesson. And he went on and ever since then he got - he sailed, oh aye, after then - after - after he reckoned he'd learnt 
his lesson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who was Mr Acton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
He were - he were big coal merchant at that time but he had been in two or three different businesses, been in that - pub. The - White hart. Kept that, but he were in coal business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you come into contact with these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well only just in ordinary walking about. Not in any contract with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Why were they considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well 'cos they were prominent do you see at - like prominent at front of - other people in a way of speaking, they could - do more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who did the shopkeepers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I think they only associated with one another a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Shopkeepers at that time, the shops weren't - weren't the same as they are now you know, they - 
they keep a shop, and where they'd got no ornaments. And no fancy things. They just took - came in rough hamper and some on 'em stood on floor and that'd be - be enough. Tea thrown in window. All }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 jumbled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  together. You got - that were half - you could get y
our stuff cheaper there than what you could at these shops that done a bit about - window dressing, you see, then. Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who did the teachers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh I've no idea, I'm sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What about farmers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well farmers, you used to hardly see them. Not the - not the - not the real farmers. Not the - farm owners like. You - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 you never}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 see 'em out hardly. Mind you he would be going out - to different - different places than where - than where you was going. You see? His outings would be a different than me, in our - in our younger life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who did the employers associate with? The Robinson's and Farr's counted as employers did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well, they was - Robinson's and Farr's, they were employers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 so}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  they - they owned the brewery. They were the - biggest brewer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did they mix with other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh no, they only mixed with - they wouldn't mix with us - as far as that goes. They'd only mix with - them as - who owned a business or - or somebody - in some other kind of business what they were associated with. Any of them sort of fellow - people.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - to be honest, biggest part of 'em what went to church for business. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - there were 
more went as regards business and - and - to - either got a job somewhere or - some'at, than what they did than went as regards }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 worshipping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You think that do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I do. I seen it. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of people went to the chapels?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - it weren't quite so many went to chapel as - the - with there being - more chapels like. There were - there was Methodist, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 Ebenezer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
, this one, Gospel Mission. Wesleyans, Congregations, Redhill Chapel and - Cross Lane and Cross Street chapel. Well you see t
hat were - you see, the chapel party - had got more places to have it sent - to go to than what the church people had. See what I mean, you either went to one or other to church, but chapel they could move about, matter of about eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did people move round the chapels or did they stick to one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Oh they used to go round. Aye. Aye. Aye, they used to go different chap else, if you go to one - one - one time and then they would be going to another the next time you knew.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No, they were - there were some - a shade different as regards - well as regards dress. Some of 'em - put on a bit more dressy than others. Always - there
 were always that. Well R mean there is today i'nt there. I mean some of 'em dressed even if they couldn't afford it you see. Others wouldn't bother, I - I'm satisfied, I've got something on and that'll do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest in the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No, not since - that - same as we've just been talking about what busted. That twist hand. According to - in my very young days I've heard 'em say about them twist hands. Used to have special rooms in pubs. Aye.
 And - have a cab to take 'em - them - the cabs then, not taxis, and - they used to be termed as a - king of pub do you see. When it were in its proper day. It's same as I say - before - that were before I - I never seen it. I've heard talk on it. And I t
hink - biggest part of it were true. Because they were doing that well - you see, they'd to - act Lord Mayor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 They were a sort of class apart from the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye. Had to act Lord Mayor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were there any other groups like that that were very special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. Don't think - I don't think - I never knowed of any. I never heard of any others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Oh aye, there was some as was - just - think were rougher than others like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 In what sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well either - either looking for a fight or anything. Picking a fight or anything. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 They'd just - they wouldn't - they wouldn't pick a fight unless there was four or five on 'em, the same as they are, want to be - if there were on
ly about two on you, you see and there were three or four of them they - they'd try pick a fight then, but they wouldn't pick a - wouldn't - if you - if they were on their own. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
And they used to have some fights then you know. Used to have some fights then. Oh aye. Lads -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Over what sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Perhaps a - well a fight, it - it had got - when you were lads it were a fight to see who - in - in our young days there used to - there used to - be a fight on that recreation ground every dinner time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was this a sort of organised fight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
No, it was a proper - proper - no kicking - aye, proper fight, if one - yes. Aye that's how they used to go on, you - get it when while we went in school. All right. We'll see who's - best when we get out. Th
en they used to go on that field and - fight it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you ever remember seeing women fight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, I've seen 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Were they drunk when they fought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, they weren't - weren't always drunk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What sort of things did they fight about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
There were few - very few women used pubs then you know. There - there were very few women used pubs. In my very young days. But them few that did - did do, they were - bad women. And they were always what used public - they don't - they didn't use pub
s same as they did - do today. Women didn't. You see, there were these pubs and there weren't a woman allowed in 'em. You see, then. Then it got as they had to allow 'em, 'cos it - 'cos it - because the - the husbands used to have to take 'em out, so it -
 
if they didn't take 'em there you'd got to take 'em somewhere else, so they had to allow women. That's how it come - comes to - be women in - in the - in the pub I'm speaking about. But the - they used to always class a woman as went in a pub - then as a 
-
 no good. And I met my wife in a pub you see, and - and - that - she didn't drink. That's what I say. She was teetotal. She were teetotal then. And you know - when I were courting her - we used to go down to picture - picture house at - at - Milford Road,
 
I'm going to have a drink before - before I go in, are you coming? And she used to stand out - wait on me while I went and had one. Yes, never went - she'd only just been in the - she'd just call in the same as I said to you, with this - friend's mother. 
And her - and that was the only time she'd been in a pub. And she never went in with me. And she never had a drink at home - 'til she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 It's really quite strange you met at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, that's what I mean. Meeting her in a pub you see. Oh I was goin
g to tell - latter part of - her life I got her to have a - bottle of Whitbread stout and then I got her to have a drop of gin - brandy. And - for a medicine. And she never - as I say, she was proper teetotaler and I met her in a pub. Aye, but she weren't
 drinking. She were drinking lemonade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So you might not have met her at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well - aye, it were just like - her going in like a coincidence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember a special distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well they always thou
ght they were bit better than others but there were no distinction. No real distinction. Oh no, there were no real distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to each other to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well my mother'd asso
ciate with - with either the toppest or the lowest. Just same. Used to go her own routine and - same with one as other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 And was your father the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Me dad was a bit more - antagonist as you might say - as regards some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Who would he be antagonistic to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well, I mean if he thought he were as anybody - if he thought anybody had done him - some - some harm sometime he always - he'd always watch him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, she never belonged anywhere. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you think she thought of herself as working class, do you think she thought in those terms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 All as I know - all as my mother used to bother with that were - used - and if anybody were in trouble handy
, a neighbour she'd be - there to help 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 So it didn't bother her much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 She didn't think about it much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No, I don't think there were any - I never knew of any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman, you mentioned that your Bible class teacher was a real gentleman?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, that were only the - that were the one and only - one and only real gentleman I met. Mr Harlow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Why do you describe him as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well, because he were honest - he never used to - differ. He were same - this Sunday to was last. The same man - every time. Now some isn't. Some isn't same man. Some's got - a different attitude altog
ether from one Sunday to another. That's how this - Mr Bramley come do you see, he - he'd got different attitude. A man as keeps to one - one theme - in my way of - watching him and - and knowing him, he's a gentleman. A man as goes any road - let him go,
 he's no - you let him go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did you remember anyone else like Mr Harlow or was he very special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well I've met others, but never one not - not - not as good as him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What about a real lady, did you ever remember anyone being described as a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well - I've met a - met some real ladies as I used to term 'em on my - when I was - going round, but I can't remember their names now, can't remember who they was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What made you think of them as real ladies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Well how they spoke to y
ou and everything. You could tell - if it were genuine. You could - you could - you tell when it were genuine - genuine. Sympathy or anything of that like but - or whether it were just - faking or - you could tell the difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Could you describe how you could tell the difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
Well, they give theirselves away, with some' at, sometimes if you - if you was regular well - they - they give theirselves with it. I mean it's same as you talking to one another. If I tried to act - somebody else fir
st time you come I've got - I've got to keep it up. See? And you - you - you - your own rough way of going on don't - don't let you, so you let yourself down. Like - in so many hours. That's how - aye, that's how it works out. You - you see - they come wi
t
h all this - bombast and - and - and - see and - and it was same as - friend of mine used to say, a liar - needs a good memory. I says, a man as speaks truth needs no memory. He says, ooh, he says, that's first time I've heard that. I said, well - now doe
s he? I said, because he ain't got this wonder - whether he's telling lies or truth. As far as he's concerned - his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 conscience}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
 is concerned he's always speaking truth. You see, so he - now if he's telling lies you've got to wonder whether it's true or it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 ain't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  - true, you see, if you've been telling lies all your life. That's how it - how it - how I look at it. And now doubt there's something to it and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Policeman? He come after me a time or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 What did he come after you for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 He come after me - for chopping a hedge down to make a bonfire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Whose hedge was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Hedges. Hedges house. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9109945\charrsid9707487 Hedge's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487  house. He lived in the orphanage where - where the - aye, in an orphanage he got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 You were cutting the hedge down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 
And it - and they were hedges, they were - about two yards wide and - and about - like nine foot high. And me and another chap, we used to go - chopping this - a few branches out for bonfire n
ight - and he - he'd never miss 'em. 'Til somebody went and shopped on you. Shopped on us. So they brought policeman up. And me dad had got one of them - butchers hatchets, cleavers as we called 'em - so I sat in chair same as sitting there, Bobby come to
 front door and Mr Hedges. So - me dad - me dad shouts, come in, and in they both come. So - this Bobby's name were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 There was a Bobby Boot wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Aye, that were Bobby Boot as helped me with bike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 This was another one was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 I
 know it, I can't - but anyway - so he follows Hedges in you know and I - so Hedges says, we've come about - him chopping hedge. He dad says, lads there, take him. So I said, I've got to go. He said, we don't want lad. He said, what do you want then? He s
a
id, we want some damages. Me dad says, you've come to the right place for damages, he says - I don't know how you're going on. Something to that effect so - he says - damages for what? He says, chopping hedge down, he says. Well where have they put 'em? H
e
 says, I don't allow him to bring none here. I weren't allowed to bring any on my land - on my garden. So Mr Hedges says, that's - that's what we want to get to know. He says, well you'll find 'em two doors away from here. In his son's garden it were. Aye
.
 His own son. And he'd neglected it and let it - let it go, so we claimed it to play on and - and make us bonfire on and he never used to say anything about it. You see? He didn't mind. It wasn't much garden. So - they went out to find out - who this - wh
o'd got this on his land and found out it were his son and they went. Let - let it drop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12336841 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 Did your mother ever say I'll call a policeman when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7612275 WM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12927729\charrsid9707487 No. Nor me dad. No. They used to give you a good hiding theirselves. Didn't that's what I
 said to - sooner - Bobby - Bobby catch me than me dad.
\par }}